	(982,134,'description','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Louis Wain</b> was an English <a title=\"Artist\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artist\">artist</a> best known for his drawings, which consistently featured <a title=\"Anthropomorphism\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthropomorphism\">anthropomorphised </a>large-eyed <a title=\"Cat\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cat\">cats</a> and kittens. In his later years he may have suffered from <a title=\"Schizophrenia\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schizophrenia\">schizophrenia</a>, which, according to some <a title=\"Psychiatrist\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychiatrist\">psychiatrists</a>, can be seen in his works.</p>'),
