	(182,2,'2014-04-25 15:45:14','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2665\" title=\"Ge-Imagination-At-Work\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Ge-Imagination-At-Work-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" />Congratulations to <a href=\"http://barkingowlsound.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Barking Owl</a> on their nomination to the 2014 AICP Shortlist for their Original Music for GE\'s gorgeous spot, \"Childlike Imagination\".  Their fantastical musical composition enhances the spirited, celestial images.  <a href=\"http://www.awardcore.com/aicp/shortlist/details.php?catID=9&amp;entID=8262&amp;subID=4300&amp;type=aicp\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> to give a listen to the nominated spot!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','AICP Nominations Are In!','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-04-25 15:45:14','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=182',293,'post','',0),
	(183,2,'2014-07-08 19:43:35','0000-00-00 00:00:00','Barking Owl  gives you something to smile about with this spot for Cricket Wireless! Their unique and playful sound design makes us want to tag along and join the fun with these joyful and animated jumping bean characters!\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">[youtube fi7G0RgqcxQ nolink]</p>','All Smiles Over Here','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-07-08 19:43:35','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=183',292,'post','',0),
	(184,2,'2006-07-06 17:09:31','2006-07-06 17:09:31','The Family made another triumphant run thru the South of France in late June, and we are happy to report that sister Diane didn’t bleed from a flesh wound this year (unfortunately Chuck Ryant didn’t have the same luck). Diane’s second annual late night/early morning doctor visit might have been prevented if she hadn’t made a certain boat trip to St. Tropez and eaten the Fruit of the Sea (special thanks to a company that will remain nameless…but it rhymes with Wino and the guy’s name sounds like Rhagonheim). In other news, Chris left the Villa (pussy) just in time to avoid the 2 masked burglars who tried to break into the cave at 2 in the morning. Brave Family member Eriks fought them off with a hearty scream and a firm shake of the metal door. We discovered that cockles taste better in the South of France. At the Backyard Villa party, the champagne flowed and the uncountable legion of rep whores and wannabes and fabulous agency creatives all had fun (thank you Stu Dearnley for pointing out how hazardous the front staircase can be when you are raving drunk and the stairs are wet). Some significant sightings in Cannes: Transistor EP (and <a href=\"http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&amp;friendID=45641236\" target=\"_blank\">Marching Teeth</a> frontman) Damon Meena’s tattoos on his legs, Backyarder Blair Stribley at the Gutter Bar at 4:00AM, JTH in the vortex, John and Peter at the villa (wait, we never saw them), Wyatt aka “the new Kohl,” brother Jimmy Waldron defending the USA goal for the hapless American team (we love THEM REPS.)…Cannes it be topped? Check back next year to see.','Cannes you dig it?','','publish','open','open','','cannes-you-dig-it','','','2006-07-06 17:09:31','2006-07-06 17:09:31','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=184',291,'post','',0),
	(185,2,'2006-07-09 21:20:58','2006-07-09 21:20:58','<img title=\"Picture 1.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Picture%201.jpg\" alt=\"Picture 1.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"196\" />\r\n\r\nBackyard director Aaron Stoller has just completed a new comedy campaign for Chevy. Please check out <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=f2f8ad58c433e6abce703d134b91237f\" target=\"_blank\">Principles and Say No </a>to see two of the spots in this package. Next up for Aaron: new Ad Council work out of Mullen.','RANDY WHO?','','publish','open','open','','randy-who','','','2006-07-09 21:20:58','2006-07-09 21:20:58','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=185',290,'post','',0),
	(186,2,'2006-07-11 21:21:40','2006-07-11 21:21:40','Transistor director Saiman Chow showed the true color of his soul in his incredible and dark and disturbingly satisfying adicolor “Black” film. Several thousand crazed Pandas have already downloaded the film to their ipods, and the National Association of Fish That Breathe (NAFTB) has called for Adidas to pull the film. “Black” has been in every publication and on every website in the world, but if you still haven’t seen it yet, please feel free to watch it <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G4W45qKGiz4\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.  The Family gives this film an NC-17 rating but you should decide for yourself.\r\n\r\n<img title=\"gun hold.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/gun%20hold.jpg\" alt=\"gun hold.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"216\" />','THE FAMILY\'S FAVORITE COLOR IS BLACK!','','publish','open','open','','the-familys-favorite-color-is-black','','','2006-07-11 21:21:40','2006-07-11 21:21:40','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=186',289,'post','',0),
	(187,2,'2006-07-14 21:23:13','2006-07-14 21:23:13','In Sweden they have a really great tradition – a father takes off from work for three months paternity leave when a new baby is born. Unfortunately, it happens even if you are a super-talented director, and everybody is talking about your new LAFA films, and you’ve just shot HONDA in the US, and your stock couldn’t be higher. But here at The Family we are not bitter. Nope. We are just so happy that Jesper Ericstam is coming back to work in August. Congratulations on your new Family member, Jesper. Now get back to work!','I SHALL CALL HIM \"MINI ME\"!','','publish','open','open','','i-shall-call-him-mini-me','','','2006-07-14 21:23:13','2006-07-14 21:23:13','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=187',288,'post','',0),
	(188,2,'2006-07-20 21:24:52','2006-07-20 21:24:52','On a recent overnight stay in Chappaqua, Diane’s dog Cha Cha (pictured in Adidas warmup jacket) and Chris’s dog Fez waited for New Cat (We think her name is Cocoa?) to finish all of the dog food before they would eat their dinners. Later that evening, a firefly terrified Fez and the sound of crickets freaked out Cha Cha.\r\n\r\n<img title=\"IMG_0755.JPG\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/IMG_0755.JPG\" alt=\"IMG_0755.JPG\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />','WHO HAS THE WHIMPIEST DOG, DIANE OR CHRIS? YOU BE THE JUDGE.','','publish','open','open','','who-has-the-whimpiest-dog-diane-or-chris-you-be-the-judge','','','2006-07-20 21:24:52','2006-07-20 21:24:52','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=188',287,'post','',0),
