	(190,2,'2006-08-01 21:26:15','2006-08-01 21:26:15','<img title=\"Chacha surfing.jpeg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Chacha%20surfing.jpeg\" alt=\"Chacha surfing.jpeg\" width=\"340\" height=\"255\" />\r\n\r\nProving that she is NOT the wimpiest Family dog, Cha Cha is pictured above hanging ten with ease. Granted, she\'s only surfed a backyard pool in East Hampton, but whatever man, a barrel is a barrel. Not only will The Chach be in the Ditch Plains line up in late August, she\'s entered in several contests along the Dirty Jersey Shore. She\'s the best in her heat so we expect big things. Cha Cha has also signed on to be the first Chihuahua to tow in on Waikiki for the upcoming feature \"Riding Giants II: Dogs of the Lords of Dogtown.\" She\'s so f\'ing rad. Check out that form, that confidence, and those really cute, big ears. She totally shreds waves created by human cannonball dives. Wait til you see it. Cha Cha Patrone can surf. What you got Fez?? Huh?? Bring it.','CHA CHA STEPS INTO LIQUID','','publish','open','open','','cha-cha-steps-into-liquid','','','2006-08-01 21:26:15','2006-08-01 21:26:15','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=190',285,'post','',0),
