	(192,2,'2006-08-20 21:28:24','2006-08-20 21:28:24','<img title=\"Veggie.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Veggie.jpg\" alt=\"Veggie.jpg\" width=\"314\" height=\"235\" />\r\n\r\nFirst it was Panda killing his best friend Fish in the adicolor film. Now Transistor Studios is at it again. For this new MTV 10 Spot clip, the Studio (with creative director James Price) laid waste to a hapless band of vegetables with a mallet of death. Are we the first to notice a disturbing trend here? We’ll keep you posted. In the meantime, Mr. Price has requested Family dog Cha Cha for the launch spots of MTV Tres next week. Let\'s hope the mallet of death doesn\'t meet her, or Diane would be really sad.','VEGGIE BAND MEETS WOLFMOTHER, AND THE RESULT IS SQUASH.','','publish','open','open','','veggie-band-meets-wolfmother-and-the-result-is-squash','','','2006-08-20 21:28:24','2006-08-20 21:28:24','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=192',283,'post','',0),
	(193,2,'2006-09-04 21:29:17','2006-09-04 21:29:17','<img title=\"invincible_02.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/invincible_02.jpg\" alt=\"invincible_02.jpg\" width=\"271\" height=\"400\" />\r\n\r\nOr are we just excited about director/cameraman Ericson Core signing to Backyard?? It\'s not every day that you get to represent a top cinematographer turned hot director who\'s responsible for the number one movie in America! That\'s right, Ericson Core, director (and cinematographer) of \"Invincible\" starring Mark Walhberg, is now available for commercial work via Backyard Productions. Well actually, he is directing and shooting CBS\'s \"The Courier\" in Prague right now, but he\'s available just after that. For a little while. So get him while you can! Ericson was also the cinematographer on \"Daredevil,\" \"The Fast and the Furious\" (the first one, not that Tokyo crap), and Mel Gibson\'s \"Payback.\" Ericson is particulary proud of being Mel\'s choice on that film despite Core\'s compassion and tolerance of all world religions. It really speaks to his talents. If you haven\'t seen Invincible yet, check it out in the theater.\r\n\r\nTo honor Ericson and his box office hit, here are some lyrics from another invincible hit by the legendary Pat Benatar:\r\n\r\nWon\'t anybody help us?/What are we running for?/When there\'s no where, no where we can run to anymore/We can\'t afford to be innocent/Stand up and face the enemy/It\'s a do or die situation/We will be Invincible/And with the power of conviction/There is no sacrifice/It\'s a do or die situation/We will be Invincible.\r\n\r\nThat really says it all. Thank you Pat. Welcome Ericson.','WE ARE NOW INVINCIBLY FAST AND FURIOUS, LOOKING FOR PAYBACK','','publish','open','open','','we-are-now-invincibly-fast-and-furious-looking-for-payback','','','2006-09-04 21:29:17','2006-09-04 21:29:17','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=193',282,'post','',0),
	(194,2,'2006-09-06 21:30:31','2006-09-06 21:30:31','<img title=\"ironmanlogo.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/logo.jpg\" alt=\"ironmanlogo.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"96\" />\r\n\r\nAs a former, amateur, mediocre triathlete, Sister Diane is truly in awe of our new Family Member...Cut + Run editor Chris Hellman. Or should we say Cut + Run editor and IRONMAN, Chris Hellman?!?! That\'s right, Chris Hellman literally Cuts AND Runs. And he does really well at both. But people, he\'s a not just an Ironman. He\'s a<a href=\"http://ironman.com/events/ironman/worldchampionship\" target=\"_blank\"> Kona, Hawaii </a>Ironman. The ultimate race! The ultimate challenge! 2.4 mi. swim + 112 mi. bike + 26.2 mi. run in the tropical mountains!  This guy\'s for reals.  We have no idea when the dude gets time to train because he is always cutting. Chris brings his Ironman endurance and intensity to the editing room and has a very loyal following because of it. He\'s a gem of a guy and a brilliant editor. We are stoked to have him on our team. However, due to his insane work schedule and obvious athleticism, we think he might be super human. Plus, there is evidence that leads us to believe that he might not require any sleep. We are closely observing him to prove our theory. In the meantime, you should closely observe his editorial work and book him while you can!','REMEMBER TO TAKE YOUR IRON, MAN.','','publish','open','open','','remember-to-take-your-iron-man','','','2006-09-06 21:30:31','2006-09-06 21:30:31','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=194',281,'post','',0),
	(195,2,'2006-09-20 21:31:36','2006-09-20 21:31:36','Backyard Productions is home to 100% of the Latvian executive producers working in the marketplace today.','FACTOID','','publish','open','open','','factoid','','','2006-09-20 21:31:36','2006-09-20 21:31:36','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=195',280,'post','',0),
	(196,2,'2006-09-22 21:34:38','2006-09-22 21:34:38','For the 5th year in a row, Backyard has been named to this exclusive list. See it for yourself in this month\'s Creativity Magazine. Or, read it here:\r\n\r\n<em>Backyard</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Founded 1989</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Roster: Aaron Stoller, John Immesoete, Rob Sanders, Jesper Ericstam, Rob Pritts, Kevin Smith, Michael Chaves, Don Rase, Steve Burrows, Jeffrey Karoff, Tim Abshire, Chace Strickland, Nick Piper, Jan Wentz, Ericson Core. Principals: Roy Skillicorn, Blair Stribley.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>For a company that remains as down-to-earth as you\'d expect from a name like Backyard, the shop has plowed ahead in asserting its position in the changing media landscape. Spots remained fresh and funny, as on Capital One via Rob Pritts, Metro PCS directed by John Immesoete or BK and Chevy from newcomer Aaron Stoller. Ericson Core, director of the Mark Wahlberg vehicle \"Invincible\" signed on, while the company also beefed up its non-spot profile with notable contributions from affiliates Transistor, whose Saiman Chow crafted the morbidly cuddly \"Black\" panda for adicolor; and from content division Seed, which backed a blockbuster series of webfilms for Sea-Doo, out of Cramer Krasselt, featuring Backyard talents Michael Chaves and Jeffrey Karoff.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWell done, Backyard. Being that they are so good at getting on top lists, Backyard\'s next goal is to make David Letterman\'s Top Ten List. We really like it when Dave throws the pencil and breaks the fake window. Plus, who doesn\'t love canned ham?!','BACKYARD NAMED TO CREATIVITY\'S TOP 25 PRODUCTION COMPANY LIST, AGAIN.','','publish','open','open','','backyard-named-to-creativitys-top-25-production-company-list-again','','','2006-09-22 21:34:38','2006-09-22 21:34:38','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=196',279,'post','',0),
	(197,2,'2006-10-14 21:37:48','2006-10-14 21:37:48','<img title=\"shaft.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/shaft.jpg\" alt=\"shaft.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"225\" />\r\n\r\nWe love it when two distant Family Members (2nd cousins in this case) come together to create something beautiful. It happened earlier this month when Backyard director John Immesoete helmed two humorous performance spots for IFC, and asked Merritt Duff from Cut+Run do the editing. (The team at Cut+Run also added sound design and finished). Check out the spots<a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=84a1745d8af956e71e577265f26a0f5b\" target=\"_blank\"> here</a>.','ALL IN THE FAMILY','','publish','open','open','','all-in-the-family','','','2006-10-14 21:37:48','2006-10-14 21:37:48','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=197',278,'post','',0),
	(198,2,'2006-11-02 21:42:41','2006-11-02 21:42:41','<img title=\"animal.grid.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/animal.grid.jpg\" alt=\"animal.grid.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"225\" />\r\n\r\nA hunter-gatherer society is one whose primary subsistence method involves the direct procurement of tastily designed moving morsels of color and shapes from the wild, using foraging and hunting, without significant recourse to the domestication of either. The demarcation between hunter-gatherers and other design companies, which rely more upon domestication, is not a clean one, as many contemporary societies use a combination of both strategies to obtain the design required to sustain themselves. Hunter-gatherer societies also tend to have non-hierarchical, egalitarian social structures, which allow inventiveness to flow.\r\n\r\nWe are excited to announce that The Family has taken on HunterGatherer for worldwide representation. HunterGatherer is the Lower East Side-based animation and design collective known for it’s intelligent storytelling with deceptively simple filmmaking. Director Todd St. John leads a studio that is known for it’s woodworking, printmaking, clothing, skateboard design, and moving videos. HunterGatherer’s Nike interactive films, <a href=\"http://www.huntergatherer.net/project.php?id=5&amp;cat=0\" target=\"_blank\">One Time Only,</a> were featured on adcritic.com last month, and the studio is currently finishing production on ebay out of BBDO NY. In addition, Todd will be speaking at the <a href=\"http://www.aigany.org/events/details/?event=07IB\" target=\"_blank\">AIGA</a> in NYC on November 15th. HunterGatherer is available to handle a select few tasty jobs.','A FAMILY FRIENDLY LESSON IN EARLY MAN','','publish','open','open','','a-family-friendly-lesson-in-early-man','','','2006-11-02 21:42:41','2006-11-02 21:42:41','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=198',277,'post','',0),
	(199,2,'2006-11-30 22:05:47','2006-11-30 22:05:47','<img title=\"mini.jesper.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/mini.jesper.jpg\" alt=\"mini.jesper.jpg\" width=\"257\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\nWhen we last left off, our favorite Swede had just returned from a six month paternity leave (see 7.14.06 entry). In this latest installment, Jesper\'s got a kick ass new reel and is back with a hunger for good scripts that rivals his infant son\'s hunger for bottles and binkies. His latest spot for <a href=\"http://www.backyard.com/qt/eri_seb_foreveryoung.mov\" target=\"_blank\">SEB</a> made Adcritic\'s Top 20 (rated a whopping 82!) and he\'s become a darling of industry press (click to see articles in <a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/media/Media/creativity.mag.06.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">Creativity</a> and <a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/media/Media/boards.mag.iss.IIvol7.oct06.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">Boards</a> .) He\'s like the Scarlett Johansson of commercial directors and we feel that next Woody Allen will want to co direct a branded content piece with him, but only if it shoots in London- Woody is so over New York.','I WILL CALL HIM MINI ME, PT 2','','publish','open','open','','i-will-call-him-mini-me-pt-2','','','2006-11-30 22:05:47','2006-11-30 22:05:47','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=199',276,'post','',0),
	(200,2,'2006-12-10 22:43:12','2006-12-10 22:43:12','<img title=\"ianball2.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/ianball2.jpg\" alt=\"ianball2.jpg\" width=\"309\" height=\"412\" />\r\n\r\nWe thought it was about time we gave mention to our intern superstar Ian Riccaboni, aka Baby Brother, aka Boy Wonder. Ian’s list of achievements just seems to keep on going and going. He’s like the Energizer bunny but way less annoying and not as pink. Not only is this Sophomore the starting first baseman of the NYU Varsity baseball team but he has just been voted The President of the Steinhardt Class of 2009! Watch out, Hillary, it’s Riccaboni for President! Ian can also add budding musician to his long list of talents, recently winning his dorm talent show. AND he’s our intern, and let me tell you that Brother Chris works him to the bone and has flagrantly violated many labor laws. (Just kidding U.S. Gov’t.) Between his musical talents, his academic success and his batting stance, Ian has all the bases covered...keep your eyes peeled because this kid is sure to hit the big time!','Who is Ian and Why?','','publish','open','open','','who-is-ian-and-why','','','2006-12-10 22:43:12','2006-12-10 22:43:12','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=200',275,'post','',0),
	(201,2,'2006-12-19 22:46:09','2006-12-19 22:46:09','Here\'s a picture of Jon Arnold, from Mullen NC, who recently worked with Michael Chaves at Backyard on Embarq.  He seems to really be enjoying his NEW FAMILY TRACK JACKET.  Also notice how he added the perfect touch of additional swag, a coveted Backyard Tee. A subtle touch that speaks volumes.\r\n\r\n<img title=\"jon arnold.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/jon%20arnold.jpg\" alt=\"jon arnold.jpg\" width=\"286\" height=\"216\" />\r\n\r\nWell done, Jon! We hereby name you Family Member of the Day. (Thanks for the picture, Mickey).\r\n\r\nSome of you, and you know who you are, have yet to receive your Family holiday gifts. Well, Santa is still making his rounds so keep checking that mailbox, friends, and if a package doesn\'t appear in the next few days, drop us an email.','JON ARNOLD: FAMILY MEMBER OF THE DAY','','publish','open','open','','jon-arnold-family-member-of-the-day','','','2006-12-19 22:46:09','2006-12-19 22:46:09','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=201',274,'post','',0),
	(202,2,'2007-01-09 22:49:19','2007-01-09 22:49:19','<img title=\"Huga_Amp.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Huga_Amp.jpg\" alt=\"Huga_Amp.jpg\" width=\"480\" height=\"120\" />\r\n\r\nHi. We had a fun holiday break. Diane threw a New Year\'s Eve party in the office and completely trashed it. Chris went up to Stratton to try the new winter sport mudboarding. Holly was sick. Ian was in Florida. How was your vacation?\r\n\r\nTo start 2007 off on the right foot, we are featuring this brand new <a href=\"http://www.huntergatherer.net/project.php?id=33&amp;cat=0\" target=\"_blank\">AMP campaign </a>from HunterGatherer and BBDO NY. We love the handmade, home cooked, all-natural goodness that HuGa brings to their work. And their sense of humor...these spots are little nuggets of fun. Can you tell that we love HunterGatherer?\r\n\r\nThanks to BBDO family members Ed Zazzera, Gerard Caputo, Eric Silver and Craig Duffney for coming up with such a great project to work on, and thanks to Pepsi/Mountain Dew for introducing such a delicious highly caffeinated energy drink!','Fresh Year, Fresh Work!','','publish','open','open','','fresh-year-fresh-work','','','2007-01-09 22:49:19','2007-01-09 22:49:19','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=202',273,'post','',0),
	(203,2,'2007-01-24 22:51:20','2007-01-24 22:51:20','<div>DISCLAIMER</div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nBrothers. They are both endearing and stupid. At least mine is. I love my\r\n\r\nbrother and stand by him always. But I feel he might have just commited\r\n\r\ncareer suicide with his recent PR blitz (see Adweek 1/22/07, p.30) so I just have to\r\n\r\nmake it clear...I HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH WHAT HE SAID IN ADWEEK. In fact,\r\n\r\nhere is The Family\'s official, legal stance on Chris Zander\'s quote in\r\n\r\nAdweek:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\"The (Brother\'s) review (of the Orville Redenbacher spot by CPB) doesnt\r\n\r\nwarrant ANY of the information on this site, and can make no guarantees as\r\n\r\nto its accuracy or as to the rationality of any of the opinions\r\n\r\nexpressed. Please note that the ratings the review provides solely represent\r\n\r\nthe review\'s biased interpretation and subjective opinion of the actual\r\n\r\nreviews and do not claim to accurately reflect or represent the views of the\r\n\r\nreviewers. Similarly the illustrative quotes chosen by the review are merely\r\n\r\nthose the complete review subjectively believes represent the tenor and\r\n\r\njudgment of the review as a whole. The review acknowledges (and reminds and\r\n\r\nwarns users) that they may, in fact, be entirely unrepresentative of the\r\n\r\nactual reviews by any other measure.\"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGranted, I just threw my Brother under the bus. But isn\'t that what little\r\n\r\nsiblings do? I mean first of all, he talked to the media. Totally my job! He\r\n\r\nstole it! MOM!!! Second of all, he slandered one of the top ad agencies in the world. Totally\r\n\r\nnot my idea. Third of all, although he makes a genius point about Chuck Wagon ads making\r\n\r\na come back, the resurrecting of all the little dead cowboys and horses is\r\n\r\njust sick and twisted. And I\'m not even sure it\'s funny. He crossed the\r\n\r\nline.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo, you see what I\'m dealing with. Again, The Family apologizes to Alex\r\n\r\nBogusky and his team for Chris publicly pointing out the lameness of their\r\n\r\nlatest ad for Orville Redenbacher, and would appreciate that Alex et al not\r\n\r\nhold Chris\'s slip up (which I have totally wiped my hands of) against The\r\n\r\nFamily in future business dealings.\r\n\r\n</div>','Disclaimer','','publish','open','open','','disclaimer','','','2007-01-24 22:51:20','2007-01-24 22:51:20','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=203',272,'post','',0),
	(204,2,'2007-02-15 16:43:11','2007-02-15 16:43:11','Everyone has their secrets. Those little tidbits of naughty that we all have captured on film. Oh come on, you know you have \'em. Don\'t act all innocent.\r\n\r\nWell, what if, and I am just sayin\' what if here, but what if that naked pic got lost...and someone found it...and the published it in a magazine?!HOLY EMBARRASSING BATMAN!\r\n\r\nWell, my x-rated friends, there is such a magazine. It is called Dirty Found and it is the salacious sister rag of Found magazine.  Dirty F wants you to know that when you tuck that nudey polaroid into that old shoebox and then donate said old shoes to Good Will, some Dirty Staffer will be there to find it and share it with the masses....\r\n\r\nTo promote their lewdness, the magazine turned to our very own resident potty mouth, Aaron Stoller, to direct some HILARIOUS virals. That guy is just wrong on so many levels, and he really found is calling....it\'s to be Dirty...and really, really funny.\r\n\r\nCheck out the films on Adcritic, youtube, \'Boards, or <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=a6bc683d6e77ae65703f81ad579caf1d\" target=\"_blank\">right here</a>.','DIRTY... FOUND','','publish','open','open','','dirty-found','','','2007-02-15 16:43:11','2007-02-15 16:43:11','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=204',271,'post','',0),
	(205,2,'2007-02-23 00:40:17','2007-02-23 00:40:17','December 2006 marked the end of my third semester at NYU and my first semester at the Family. As per my contractual obligations, I have been asked to compose a short report on my experiences, responsibilities, and duties as an intern, accentuating the good and ignoring the bad of my first four months at the Family. I have also been asked by Holly not to mention the time we disrupted the Kraemer Company next door by blasting Justin Timberlake around Christmas time. I guess Chris and Diane still don’t know about that. And with that said, here is my report:\r\n\r\nI know Staples. The one on 6th and 22nd, Park and 25th, and Union Square West, I have been to them all. And all for different reasons: for stamps, for bubble mailers, and even for bottled water. Each of them has the same items, and yet, I like to add spice to my life. That is the way I do things. Of my various tasks, getting the bottled water was the most confusing. I think Holly was trying to break me. To test my strength, she sent me to the 6th and 22nd one to get bottled water. Little did she know my 16 inch pythons stood up to the arduous one avenue and two street walk. I proved to her and the office that day that I am the ultimate endurance athlete. Iron Man? More like the Tin Man.\r\nMy first semester at the Family has been full of similar such tests. Success comes naturally to me. On a daily basis, I am able to hand packages to the messenger, as well as determine how much petty cash is necessary to pay the deliveryman who brings lunch. You know those awesome Family track jackets you got? I put together those 500 cardboard boxes they shipped-in, IN ONLY 5 WORKDAYS TIME! Sometimes, just for fun, I put little yellow stickers on the reels we send out just because I feel like it. I average 20 every eight minutes. These challenges lead me to confidently proclaim that my mental capacity is only dwarfed by the planet-moon Endor and that I have better hands than a Latin Lover.\r\nI feel like my bosses recognize my exemplary work, too. Let me put it this way, and Holly, don’t get too jealous, but I’ve got the only computer in the office that not only is not on the wireless network, but also doesn’t have a power adaptor.\r\nAnd each one of my bosses is uniquely terrific. I am privileged enough to have Diane let me play with and walk her dog Cha-Cha. She’s a great dresser and has exquisite taste. What a great girl, that Cha-Cha is. As for Chris, I think I made him mad the other day when I laughed when he said the name of a male enhancement product when talking about pitching, so I’ll just say this: Chris Zander is the best boss ever!!!!\r\nBut yeah, I’ve been pretty successful. After reading this, it should come as no surprise that I’m pretty much the greatest intern in the history of Earth. I have the most internal fortitude, internal instincts, and internacity. Sometimes, I sit and silently thank Richard and Shelly Riccaboni for birthing me to the earth so that I can do my thing. Chris, Diane, and Holly should do the same.','BABY BROTHER IAN CHIMES IN:','','publish','open','open','','baby-brother-ian-chimes-in','','','2007-02-23 00:40:17','2007-02-23 00:40:17','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=205',270,'post','',0),
	(206,2,'2007-05-16 00:41:18','2007-05-16 00:41:18','Hi. In case anyone was wondering, we have a penthouse office. It\'s sick. We have a killer view and nice furniture. We have cocktails at sunset. No one has a better office than us. Nor does anyone have more fun or more success in their office than we do. We rule.\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Oh PS: We also get Fresh Direct, how f\'in cool is that?</div>\r\n</div>','SWEET 1701: WE HAVE A PENTHOUSE OFFICE','','publish','open','open','','sweet-1701-we-have-a-penthouse-office','','','2007-05-16 00:41:18','2007-05-16 00:41:18','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=206',269,'post','',0),
	(207,2,'2007-05-23 00:43:09','2007-05-23 00:43:09','Give it up, give it up one time. Aaron Stoller is up on AdCritic under \"The Latest\" with his MTV Movie Awards spot \"Will.\"\r\n\r\nGo check it out.\r\n\r\nAnd vote highly for it because it\'s HILARIOUS.\r\n\r\nAnd then pass it around so it gets the good lovin\' it deserves. Word.\r\n\r\nCONGRATS to our Aaron on a killer job and CONGRATS to MTV writers and Family friends Kim Nguyen &amp; Andy Carrigan for a spectacularly written campaign.\r\n\r\nThe entire campaign will soon be available for your viewing pleasure on The Family Website.\r\n\r\nthanks &amp; love,-the family','TAINT THAT THE TRUTH','','publish','open','open','','taint-that-the-truth','','','2007-05-23 00:43:09','2007-05-23 00:43:09','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=207',268,'post','',0),
	(208,2,'2007-07-17 16:18:37','2007-07-17 16:18:37','Not only are trains the greenest way to travel, they are a great place to interact with people too, and provide a wonderful opportunity to take some time for yourself or to simply observe humanity and nature. All while getting where you need to go. Isn\'t that just beautiful? Don\'t you want to go get a train ticket right now and go somewhere? Well, if you don\'t, this spot for <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=5bece2557cc91459e22be02a58e9943b\" target=\"_blank\">Swedish Railway</a> by our very own Jesper Ericstam will make you want to get your hobo sack and go ride the rails. And the David Bowie track is the perfect inspiring touch to the stories Jesper unfolds. Enjoy.\r\n\r\nPS: you can also view this spot on AdCritic...or the new Creativity Online which launched today.','PEOPLE GET READY, A TRAIN\'S A COMIN\'','','publish','open','open','','people-get-ready-a-trains-a-comin','','','2007-07-17 16:18:37','2007-07-17 16:18:37','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=208',267,'post','',0),
	(209,2,'2007-07-18 16:19:49','2007-07-18 16:19:49','Congrats to Todd St. John and his team at HunterGatherer for their win at the One Club/One Show Design Awards. HuGa\'s \"One Time Only\" series for Nike won a <a href=\"http://www.oneclub.org/os/osd/showcase/?year=2007&amp;id=6456\" target=\"_blank\">GOLD</a> in the campaign category for Broadcast Design. YAY!!!!!','HUNTERGATHERER FINDS GOLD','','publish','open','open','','huntergatherer-finds-gold','','','2007-07-18 16:19:49','2007-07-18 16:19:49','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=209',266,'post','',0),
	(210,2,'2007-07-19 16:20:35','2007-07-19 16:20:35','Just as a follow up note, the campaign that Aaron Stoller directed for the MTV Music Awards is featured in this month\'s (July 2007) issue of Creativity Magazine. See? We told you it was really f\'ing funny. Congrats to Aaron and writers Kim Nguyen and Andy Carrigan for a job well done. To see the campaign, click <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=e15a84d9d38c59af6e9c122292cff5c9\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.','TAINT THAT THE TRUTH, pt 2','','publish','open','open','','taint-that-the-truth-pt-2','','','2007-07-19 16:20:35','2007-07-19 16:20:35','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=210',265,'post','',0),
	(211,2,'2007-09-05 16:24:30','2007-09-05 16:24:30','We\'ve been repping Ericson for exactly one year, so today seems like a good time to tell you what\'s been happening with one of our favorite talents.\r\n\r\nThe best way is to start with his recent work. Ericson has just completed this adrenaline-pumping visual spot for the<a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=6b4eb96fa56e653f2eb34fc49b85ceb5\" target=\"_blank\"> BMW</a> 5 series, this beautiful storytelling campaign for <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=abfc1ea73fd643858f3aff0c1f38f977\" target=\"_blank\">Unicel</a>, and this lyrical sheetmetal lullaby for <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=1cbea40e3e9fb5482b72b830fc920943\" target=\"_blank\">Buick</a>. In an age when almost all directors have to \"choose a major\" and specialize, or be a sad-ass non-working chump, Ericson has moved seamlessly &amp; confidently from one genre to the other, bringing every one of his incredible skills as a dp and accomplished feature film director to all of his commercial shoots. We are so happy that some good agencies have been open-minded enough to take a chance on him in his first year with us, and we are excited for his future. Next up on his plate is a humanity driven/storytelling commercial for HIP out of Hill, Holliday NY.','ERICSON CORE. ONE YEAR LATER.','','publish','open','open','','ericson-core-one-year-later','','','2007-09-05 16:24:30','2007-09-05 16:24:30','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=211',264,'post','',0),
	(212,2,'2007-09-07 16:25:50','2007-09-07 16:25:50','It was a beautiful afternoon yesterday. At 4:14PM, we were working in our office when Diane, who was on the phone with Vera, noticed that one of those old water towers you see on the roofs in NYC had ruptured across the street. Water was gushing everywhere.\r\n\r\nWe panicked. Should we call somebody? Who should we call? Were we in danger?\r\n\r\nAfter about a minute, we realized we were 300 feet away, and many floors above (see article SWEET 1701: WE HAVE A PENTHOUSE OFFICE), so we probably weren\'t in any danger, and we just calmed down. We contemplated warning Mackenzie Cutler, but then we decided not to. So we just watched.\r\n\r\nI tried to take a picture with my iphone but it didn\'t come out so well, so I\'ve asked Family Friend Vin from <a href=\"http://www.romeoempire.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Romeo Empire Design</a> to create a dramatization and show you the situation. Here it is:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img title=\"spill2.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/spill2.jpg\" alt=\"spill2.jpg\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" />','WOODEN WATER TOWER EXPLODES (AND MAKES THINGS WET)','','publish','open','open','','350','','','2007-09-07 16:25:50','2007-09-07 16:25:50','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=212',263,'post','',0),
	(213,2,'2007-09-23 16:26:46','2007-09-23 16:26:46','Three years ago Diane Patrone and Chris Zander decided to adopt each other as Brother and Sister and made repping history...The Family was born. It\'s been a fantastic three years, and we\'d like to thank all our Family Members for making this the best Family ever.\r\n\r\nTo celebrate, we invited some of our NYC based Family and Friends over for some birthday cake and champers last week. Being that Diane has discovered she has seven major food allergies** and subsequently eats like an alternative-holistic-organic-tree-hugging-gluten-free-freak, she made us all eat a special cupcakes from<a href=\"http://www.babycakesnyc.com/\" target=\"_blank\"> Babycakes Bakery </a>in Nolita and drink organic wine. It sucked. But it was still fun to see everyone and celebrate. HAPPY BIRTHDAY US!!!!\r\n\r\n(Diane actually ordered two delicious \"normal\" birthday cakes from <a href=\"http://www.crumbsbakeshop.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Crumbs Bakery</a> in addition to the Vegan-freak cupcakes. We have some left over and Chris and Ian have been eating it twice a day all week. Yum.)','THE FAMILY CELEBRATES ITS WHEAT- FREE, GLUTEN- FREE, REFINED SUGAR-FREE THIRD BIRTHDAY','','publish','open','open','','the-family-celebrates-its-wheat-free-gluten-free-refined-sugar-free-third-birthday','','','2007-09-23 16:26:46','2007-09-23 16:26:46','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=213',262,'post','',0),
	(214,2,'2007-10-01 16:28:00','2007-10-01 16:28:00','<img title=\"blackIrisWH.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/blackIrisWH.jpg\" alt=\"blackIrisWH.jpg\" width=\"230\" height=\"137\" />\r\n\r\nWe are about to start a revolution. A musical one. We have signed a new music company that is so kick ass, so rockin\', that what is about to happen in the AD WORLD can only be described as a revolution. A revolution in rock, and in how rock is used to make people wanna buy shit. HELLS YEAH!\r\n\r\nThink iPhone Launch but with awesome rock.\r\n\r\nIf you don\'t catch our insurgent drift, here\'s a little help from Wikipedia:\"A revolution (from Late Latin revolutio which means \"a turn around\") is a significant change that usually occurs in a relatively short period of time.\"\r\nMeaning, you won\'t know what hit you. \"Variously defined revolutions have been happening throughout human history. They vary in terms of numbers of their participants (revolutionaries)...\"\r\n...aka THE FAMILY...\r\n\"...means employed by them, duration, motivating ideology and many other aspects. They may result in a socio-political change in the socio-political institutions, or a major change in a culture or economy.\" Yeah, that. ALL that. That\'s what we\'re doing. Black Iris!\r\n\r\nWatch out, the revolution is coming to you.','THE REVOLUTION IS UPON US','','publish','open','open','','the-revolution-is-upon-us','','','2007-10-01 16:28:00','2007-10-01 16:28:00','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=214',261,'post','',0),
	(215,2,'2007-10-10 16:29:31','2007-10-10 16:29:31','Because we rep awesome companies.','DIANE IS EXCITED','','publish','open','open','','diane-is-excited','','','2007-10-10 16:29:31','2007-10-10 16:29:31','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=215',260,'post','',0),
	(216,2,'2007-10-18 16:31:19','2007-10-18 16:31:19','<img title=\"lqr-logo.gif\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/lqr-logo.gif\" alt=\"lqr-logo.gif\" width=\"160\" height=\"134\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHI.\r\nIt\'s Diane. And I just wanted to say that I like my job. Why? Because currently it\'s allowing me to blog, poolside, in Palm Springs.\r\n\r\nI\'m here on business, for the annual Backyard Sales Summit which starts on Saturday. (Yes, I know it\'s only Thursday but a girl needs some R&amp;R. And I told you I am doing work, it\'s just that I am in a bikini and applying SPF 30 while doing it.)\r\n\r\nIt\'s my fourth BSS and I am pretty excited about it. It\'s a time where we reflect on all the great things Backyard accomplished this year (see previous postings) and strategize about how to do even better next year. It\'s inspirational. Especially when it takes place at a <a href=\"http://www.laquintaresort.com/\" target=\"_blank\">luxury resort</a> in the Southern Californian desert. Did I mention that it\'s a comfortable 92 degrees here?\r\n\r\nWhat\'s it in New York? Raining? Yeah, not here. Here, I\'m on a chaise, using the wifi by the jacuzzi just outside my bungalow. The resort grounds are exquisite and I\'ve just learned that in addition to the pool right outside my door, there are 41 more! I plan on lounging by every single one of them. Oops, I mean plan on WORKING DILIGENTLY by every single one of them. IN MY BIKINI.\r\n\r\nStay tuned to this internet website location for more sun-kissed, desert-vibed postings and new work from Backyard, Cut + Run, loyalkaspar, and other exciting Family news. There\'s a lot going on, it\'s just happening poolside. WORD.\r\n\r\nOh PS: Chris is here too, he\'s golfing. Figures.','DIANE LIKES HER JOB','','publish','open','open','','diane-likes-her-job','','','2007-10-18 16:31:19','2007-10-18 16:31:19','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=216',259,'post','',0),
	(217,2,'2007-10-24 16:32:56','2007-10-24 16:32:56','Congratulations to Backyard (and sister company Transistor Studios) for being recognized again as one of the best production companies in the world in Creativity Magazine\'s September 2007 issue. Click <a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/media/Media/BYPCreativitySept070001%5B1%5D.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> to see the article.','BACKYARD NAMED TO CREATIVITY\'S TOP 25 PRODUCTION COMPANY LIST AGAIN','','publish','open','open','','backyard-named-to-creativitys-top-25-production-company-list-again-2','','','2007-10-24 16:32:56','2007-10-24 16:32:56','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=217',258,'post','',0),
	(218,2,'2007-11-19 16:33:42','2007-11-19 16:33:42','This is Aaron Stoller\'s first son. His parents (said Aaron and Joanna \"Joey\" Gold) have had nine freaking months to pick out a name for him, but for some reason they never got around to it so we are calling him To Be Named Stoller, TBN for short. Let\'s hope it doesn\'t stick or else he\'s headed for a major complex. Anyway, Ad World, here\'s introducing the adorable TBN Stoller!! CONGRATS to Aaron and Joey on an amazing little bundle of boy joy. YAY!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img title=\"TBN.jpg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/TBN.jpg\" alt=\"TBN.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"335\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTBN STOLLER\r\n6lbs 7oz\r\n19.5 inches long and strong\r\n\r\n11/18/07\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHAPPY BIRTHDAY TBN!!!!','TBN','','publish','open','open','','tbn','','','2007-11-19 16:33:42','2007-11-19 16:33:42','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=218',257,'post','',0),
	(219,2,'2007-11-20 16:34:32','2007-11-20 16:34:32','We here at The Family, while not open advocates of incest, feel that sometimes a little action within the kin is not the worst thing that could happen. In fact, we sometimes actually try to make Family Members get it on. For instance, Backyard and Cut + Run are totally doing it! They have done it like three or four times already, with some really fun and creative results. Is that wrong? It can\'t possibly be wrong, when spots like ESPN 360, BMW, and Johnnie Walker come out so right. So here\'s to incest, sometimes it does work out best.','KISSING COUSINS','','publish','open','open','','kissing-cousins','','','2007-11-20 16:34:32','2007-11-20 16:34:32','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=219',256,'post','',0),
	(220,2,'2007-11-21 16:35:18','2007-11-21 16:35:18','<img title=\"images.jpeg\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/images.jpeg\" alt=\"images.jpeg\" width=\"127\" height=\"189\" />\r\nEnjoy your Holiday meal!\r\nLove, The Family\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','HAPPY THANKSGIVING','','publish','open','open','','happy-thanksgiving','','','2007-11-21 16:35:18','2007-11-21 16:35:18','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=220',255,'post','',0),
	(221,2,'2007-11-28 16:36:32','2007-11-28 16:36:32','<img title=\"Wachovia.png\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Wachovia.png\" alt=\"Wachovia.png\" width=\"314\" height=\"234\" />\r\n\r\nI love my job. How many times in your life do you get the chance to make a connection between a fantastic creative team and an insanely talented group of directors &amp; designers, and then have the result end up on a giant video billboard in downtown LA? This just happened. Check out <a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/media/Media/wachovia_final_web.mov\" target=\"_blank\">this film</a> for Wachovia, the first in a series of six that will run exclusively at LA LIVE near the Staples Center. Created by loyalkaspar and Mullen.\r\n\r\nA nice coincidence: the drummer\'s name is Brother Love. And he really rocked.','LOYALKASPAR ROCKS LA LIVE FOR WACHOVIA!','','publish','open','open','','loyalkaspar-rocks-la-live-for-wachovia','','','2007-11-28 16:36:32','2007-11-28 16:36:32','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=221',254,'post','',0),
	(222,2,'2007-12-06 16:37:40','2007-12-06 16:37:40','<img title=\"Delta Faucets.png\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Delta%20Faucets.png\" alt=\"Delta Faucets.png\" width=\"322\" height=\"140\" />\r\n\r\nWe have an affinity for the finer things in life. We love to indulge ourselves in every possible luxury. We like to sip champagne, go to spas all day long (this is more Chris than Diane), and most of all we love....Caviar. Caviar LA that is! Our newest Family Member!\r\n\r\nCaviar\'s roster is tasty, refined, and decadently creative. Raf Wathion is currently on Ad Critic with his work for Jeep via Cutwater, and has garnered much deserved attention for his recent Lexus campaign, Duvel Beer commercial, and Bank of America spots via BBDO. Also, be on the look out for the delicious Bram Van Riet, whose work is starting to get noticed in the U.S.. Bram is going into production on Nissan out of TBWA/Chiat/Day next week.\r\n\r\nAnd there are more fine imported Caviars to discover...like Brussels director Frank Devos (who directed two of the best condom commercials ever), Thorsten Herken, Frank Van Passel and Kene ...all with spots that are making American ad mouths water. There are local flavors to savor, like LA-based music video director Keith Schofield, and Vermont native/indie film director Ben Zlotucha. Stephen Blackman, one of the great commercial directors of photography, has just directed/dp\'ed this Infiniti spot.\r\n\r\nWe look forward to sharing a bit of Caviar with you during our Champagne Screening. Details coming soon.','CAVIAR TASTE, CHAMPAGNE DREAMS','','publish','open','open','','caviar-taste-champagne-dreams','','','2007-12-06 16:37:40','2007-12-06 16:37:40','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=222',253,'post','',0),
	(223,2,'2007-12-10 16:38:36','2007-12-10 16:38:36','<img title=\"Wormie.png\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Wormie.png\" alt=\"Wormie.png\" width=\"249\" height=\"170\" />\r\n\r\nThe New York Times T Magazine commissioned Todd St John to make a short film about the act of giving. His version is twistedly revisited, and may make you rethink all the present buying this the holiday season. What he came up with is true to his evolutionary HunterGatherer style...all handmade, in camera, etc. Watch it before you go to the mall.\r\n\r\nClick here: <a href=\"http://video.on.nytimes.com/?fr_story=50f8f9d1fa1f7a909f1fbf19d618c163f90a3e83\" target=\"_blank\">Circle Squared Film</a>','GIVING TIL IT HURTS','','publish','open','open','','giving-til-it-hurts','','','2007-12-10 16:38:36','2007-12-10 16:38:36','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=223',252,'post','',0),
	(224,2,'2008-02-26 16:44:12','2008-02-26 16:44:12','<img title=\"JW Wright.png\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/JW%20Wright.png\" alt=\"JW Wright.png\" width=\"314\" height=\"194\" />\r\n\r\n1. We can finally show you Rob Sanders\'s <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=9aac61caac8dbad810d2a3081ebd630b\" target=\"_blank\">Johnnie Walker</a> spot. Shot in August 2007 (see Family website entry 8.27.07 titled CHRIS IS JEALOUS), this beautiful epic took six months to see the light of day. Rob, who refuses to use visual effects in his work, actually traveled back in time to capture these magnificent historic moments on film.\r\n\r\n2. Jesper Ericstam\'s <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=db123f0a47ad6c1ddd2eb33810b429df\" target=\"_blank\">AMF</a> Awakening commercial made the rounds on adcritic.com last month. This spot tells the story of a man who spends his whole life dreading the 7AM alarm clock until one day he wakes up to find that he is retired. Jesper and his crew had to travel forward in time, many years into the future, to accomplish this amazing shoot.\r\n\r\n3. Ericson Core just finished this <a href=\"http://backyard.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=c0d33bd3468f3eba5d51b6516a12cedf\" target=\"_blank\">UPS</a> spot. I don\'t know a heck of a lot about racing but it seems that Nascar driver <a href=\"http://www.dalejarrett.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Dale Jarrett</a> is retiring this year. Apparently Dale\'s claim to fame is that he\'s always driven a big brown UPS delivery truck in his races instead of a normal Nascar vehicle (see below). Ericson, with a small documentary crew, was on hand to see Dale\'s very last race, and captured his actual winning moment on film.\r\n\r\n<img title=\"Race truck.png\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site/images/Race%20truck.png\" alt=\"Race truck.png\" width=\"227\" height=\"150\" />','BACK(YARD) TO THE FUTURE','','publish','open','open','','backyard-to-the-future','','','2008-02-26 16:44:12','2008-02-26 16:44:12','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=224',251,'post','',0),
	(225,2,'2008-04-01 16:45:24','2008-04-01 16:45:24','We commend BLACK IRIS for putting forth their time and creativity to write a beautiful track featured in the <a href=\"http://www.wecansolveit.org/anthem\" target=\"_blank\">anthem commercial</a> for the newly launched WE CAN SOLVE IT initiative, spearheaded by Al Gore and The Martin Agency, with help from William H. Macy.\r\n\r\nThis spot is a poignant call to action for all Americans: we can actually solve the climate crisis-so what are we waiting for?!\r\n\r\nThe Facebook group, Stop Global Warming, is also involved with this initiative and has sent out a viral message to practically all of Facebook featuring the anthem spot and clips to some major news coverage about this initiative. It\'s pretty exciting and we are very proud that our Family Member, Black Iris, contributed to this project and this cause.','WE CAN SOLVE IT, MUSICALLY AT LEAST','','publish','open','open','','we-can-solve-it-musically-at-least','','','2008-04-01 16:45:24','2008-04-01 16:45:24','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=225',250,'post','',0),
	(226,2,'2008-04-23 16:46:15','2008-04-23 16:46:15','GUESS WHAT?! HunterGatherer won for a Webby Award for the animated film they created for NY Times Website. (See entry 12.10.07)\r\n\r\nCongrats HUGA.','LET\'S GET WEBBY WITH IT','','publish','open','open','','lets-get-webby-with-it','','','2008-04-23 16:46:15','2008-04-23 16:46:15','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=226',249,'post','',0),
