	(244,2,'2009-07-07 16:41:59','2009-07-07 16:41:59','We are excited that several of our directors keep getting noticed for the fantastic viral work that they\'ve put out in the past year.\r\n\r\nCaviar director Keith Schofield\'s <a href=\"http://caviar.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=5ec4fd21bec889bf3054ef8f738cb735\" target=\"_blank\">Diesel XXX</a> creation, which has been making the rounds for a while, won a Gold Lion in Cannes two weeks ago.  Congratulations Keith!  The Diesel film is one of our all time favorites, and we\'ll keep using it on your reel to scare away cautious clients.\r\n\r\nAlso in Cannes, a special jury commendation was given to Believe Media in Los Angeles for their <a href=\"http://believemedia.wiredrive.com/l/p/?presentation=723a145db3d1c89e9d98814e37b10c2f\" target=\"_blank\">Wassup \'08 \"True Vote\"</a> ad.  Charles Stone III directed and created.  This is one of the first times in Cannes history that a special award has been given to a non-advertiser supported PSA.\r\n\r\nFinally, the <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/organgrinder/2008/dec/11/top-viral-ads-2008\" target=\"_blank\">Guardian</a> newspaper came out with their list of the top 10 viral ads of 2008* and our Family members went 1, 2, and 3**.  Well done everybody!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: xx-small;\">* Top 10 virals for 2008 as compiled by GoViral based on compiling numbers of views from Youtube, Dailymotion, Metacafe, Break and Vimeo. Rankings adjusted by taking into account a \"people\'s verdict\".</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: xx-small;\">** Viral #3, which shows Kobe Bryant jumping over an Aston Martin, was created by Believe Media and director Whitey.  Whitey is no longer with Believe.</span>','THE FAMILY LIKES A GOOD VIRAL AND GOLD LIONS','','publish','open','open','','the-family-likes-a-good-viral-and-gold-lions','','','2009-07-07 16:41:59','2009-07-07 16:41:59','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=244',231,'post','',0),
