	(246,2,'2009-11-10 16:37:17','2009-11-10 16:37:17','<strong>Believe</strong> it or not, I\'m walking on air...Because there are so many awesome things happening at <strong>Believe</strong>.\r\n\r\nThis is a company that never sleeps.  In the past month <strong>Believe </strong>was named to the top 25 production companies in the world by Creativity; they signed an excellent new visual effects and storytelling director <a href=\"http://believemedia.wiredrive.com/library/preview_presentation/?p=9433f06c75a193c0acb15e3995cd36fa\" target=\"_blank\">Bruce St. Clair</a> whose very clever reel is making waves all over the place; AND they brought on the iconic and amazing<a href=\"http://believemedia.wiredrive.com/library/preview_presentation/?p=2af5f897586344e241f31087141193f3\" target=\"_blank\">Gerard de Thame</a> .\r\n\r\n<strong>Believe </strong>also produced several documentary short films for <em>Glamour Magazine\'s</em>Women of the Year series which debuted today (the six month project was spearheaded by Liz Silver, congrats Liz!), and put out yet another edition of their food magazine, <em>Edible LA.</em>\r\n\r\nOh and last month they signed feature film legend <a href=\"http://believemedia.wiredrive.com/library/preview_presentation/?p=e3874eac4514cb8ea16d6e4be4c0a8e1\" target=\"_blank\">Alex Proyas</a> <em>(The Crow, iRobot, Knowing)</em>.\r\n\r\nI\'m exhausted just typing about it. But wait, there\'s more.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://believemedia.wiredrive.com/library/preview_presentation/?p=f5c65e46211f2aca2755828e4ff63901\" target=\"_blank\">Jeff Darling</a> has added three new epic spots to his reel, spots that took him around the world TWICE.  Floria Sigismondi is back on the commercial scene after wrapping her first feature film, <a href=\"http://www.therunaways.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>The Runaways</em></a> , starring <a href=\"http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/03/05/hello-daddy-hello-mom-dakota-fanning-joins-runaways-movie/\" target=\"_blank\">Dakota 