	(319,2,'2011-12-21 21:30:44','2011-12-21 21:30:44','Backyard director <a href=\"http://noooge.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kim Nguyen</a> has just completed two new projects that are completely unrelated, yet oddly they go together like peas and carrots (or peanut butter and jelly if you don\'t like vegetables.)  The first is the promo for the new MTV series, \"I Just Want My Pants Back,\" created by a former agency copywriter, <a href=\"http://www.mtv.com/shows/i_just_want_my_pants_back/series.jhtml\" target=\"_blank\">David Rosen</a>.  Interestingly, Kim was also a copywriter before becoming a director. Kim also just collaborated with RGA, Google Labs, and MasterCard to a six piece campaign of very short but compelling narratives depicting what life will be like with the speed of Google <em><strong>Wallet</strong></em> on your <em><strong>phone</strong></em>, which some of you keep in the pockets of your <strong><em>pants.</em></strong> See where we\'re going with this??\r\n\r\nCheck out Kim\'s new work and press:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMTV \"I Just Want My Pants Back\"\r\n\r\n[wiredrive hidethumbs=\"off\" disablethumbs=\"off\" theme=\"inline-player\"]http://www.wdcdn.net/rss/presentation/library/client/mightyfilm/id/3a2e4eea60f371b1cd2b0e1821b2c5f8/[/wiredrive]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nGoogle/Mastercard Speed Campaign:\r\n\r\n[wiredrive hidethumbs=\"off\" disablethumbs=\"off\" theme=\"inline-player\"]http://www.wdcdn.net/rss/presentation/library/client/mightyfilm/id/1d5615b570d45642e723773b07bc2789/[/wiredrive]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fuelthefuture.adweek.com/video/mastercards-fast-and-furious/15456/\">Press for Google/Mastercard</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Put Google Wallet (with Mastercard Pay Pass) in Your Pants.','','publish','open','open','','put-google-wallet-with-mastercard-pay-pass-in-your-pants','','','2011-12-21 21:30:44','2011-12-21 21:30:44','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=319',163,'post','',0),
	(320,2,'2012-01-06 17:21:16','2012-01-06 17:21:16','Congrats to one of our most handsome and dashing directors, Mr. Jake Nava, who had a fantastic 2011 and first year with Believe Media. He directed spots with Janet Jackson, the cast of Glee, and starlet Georgia May Jagger. PLUS created standout, crazyamazing videos for <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qLnS-2h_nog\" target=\"_blank\">Kanye West</a> and <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hLQl3WQQoQ0&amp;feature=artistob&amp;playnext=1&amp;list=TLCu1clYIagYo\" target=\"_blank\">Adele</a>, which landed him at #5 on the <a href=\"http://music-mix.ew.com/2011/12/30/best-music-videos-2011/\" target=\"_blank\">Best Music Video Directors of 2011 list </a>by Entertainment Weekly.','JAKE NAVA, #5 on a prestigous director list, but #1 in our hearts. Either way, he wins.','','publish','open','open','','jake-nava-5-on-a-prestigous-director-list-but-1-in-our-hearts-either-way-he-wins','','','2012-01-06 17:21:16','2012-01-06 17:21:16','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=320',162,'post','',0),
