	(323,2,'2012-02-06 18:25:52','2012-02-06 18:25:52','What do The Jetsons, Speedy Gonzales, Waldo (of Where\'s Waldo fame), the Peanuts Gang, the Scooby Doo crew, Grape Ape, Voltron, and pretty much every other cartoon character we grew up with have in common? They all starred in the awesome <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j1RCplpVaQ0\" target=\"_blank\">Met Life Superbowl Ad</a>. The spot, titled <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/metlife?sk=app_242076289205114\" target=\"_blank\">\"Everyone,\"</a> was a big surprise and highlight of the game (according to the <a href=\" http://www.nytimes.com/2012/02/06/business/media/super-bowl-commercials-from-charming-to-smarmy.html?_r=1&amp;scp=6&amp;sq=metlife&amp;st=cse\" target=\"_blank\">NY Times</a> and <a href=\"http://ca.sports.yahoo.com/blogs/nfl-shutdown-corner/buzziest-super-bowl-ads-2012-040450380.html\" target=\"_blank\">others</a>) and is credited to the genius minds at Crispin, Porter+Bogusky, Psyop, and our own <strong>Black Iris Music</strong>. Metlife and the Peanuts gang have been long time collaborators, but CP+B really upped the ante (and our childhood nostalgia quotient) to drive home their client\'s motto: that every family, everywhere, should have the financial security it needs and Metlife is dedicated to creating a simple way to achieve it. <em>This</em> Family is super into that.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Superbowl is for \"Everyone\"','','publish','open','open','','the-superbowl-is-for-everyone','','','2012-02-06 18:25:52','2012-02-06 18:25:52','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=323',159,'post','',0),
