	(333,2,'2012-04-26 20:34:02','2012-04-26 20:34:02','<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1330\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1330\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1330\" title=\"Frozen Grand Central\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Screen-shot-2012-04-26-at-4.27.18-PM-300x221.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"221\" /></a>What would you do if you were just passing through Grand Central Station and suddenly, amid all the hustle bustle, hundreds of people just FROZE...Right in mid action....Spontaneously just froze....For like five minutes....And then, out of nowhere, they just started moving again and walked away? You\'d probably laugh out laud, a lot, and say \"what the hell just happened?!\" Perhaps, you\'d smile, chuckle to yourself, and emphatically say \"THAT was awesome.\" Regardless, you\'d definitely have a great story to tell all your friends and co-workers about the random and amazing experience you just had. You\'d also have Über Content\'s newest director, <a href=\"http://improveverywhere.com/charlie_todd/\" target=\"_blank\">Charlie Todd</a>, to thank for it.  Charlie is the scene causing mastermind behind some of the most genius, hilarious, creative, good-hearted pranks this city has ever seen. He is the founder of the now famous group <a href=\"http://improveverywhere.com/\" target=\"_blank\">IMPROV EVERYWHERE</a>, known for the <a href=\"http://improveverywhere.com/2008/01/31/frozen-grand-central/\" target=\"_blank\">Frozen Grand Central</a>, <a href=\"http://improveverywhere.com/2011/05/31/the-mute-button/\" target=\"_blank\">The Mute Button</a>, Human Mirror, and a host of other pranks.  Charlie pioneered the idea of \"flashmobs\" before they were even called that.\r\n\r\nFor the past 11 years, Charlie\'s been bringing groups of people together to execute an improv prank (or \"mission\" as he calls it) designed to make people smile and give them a good story to tell.  Mixing improvisational comedy, performance art, and plain old prankstering, Charlie has reintroduced the idea of random play to everyday life. His most famous work is probably <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yF9FM6KqCu4\" target=\"_blank\">No Pants Subway Day</a>, now in it\'s 12th year, it\'s grown from <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=217mhbpADN0\" target=\"_blank\">one subway car on the 6 train with 7 dudes in their underwear </a>to 3500 people without pants riding the New York City transit system, plus countless others in 59 other cities in 28 countries around the world.... all going pantless on the same day in January.\r\n\r\nAs a director, Charlie will bring this playful and creative sense of humor to create very original content.  Anything from staging a mission for a brand and capturing it on film via his strategically hidden cameras, to creating an prank as an interactive experience, Charlie\'s creates hilarious scenarios and stories that resonate with the people long after their inital experience. His fundamentals for making people laugh translate across all media.  Get to know Charlie by watching his TED talk, <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ooUqOwh-2LE\" target=\"_blank\">\"The Shared Experience of Absurdity\"</a> and then give us a call and see what he can bring to your next project. We guarantee it will be like nothing anyone\'s ever scene before (pun!).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1326\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1326\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1326\" title=\"&quot;Quadruplets&quot;\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Screen-shot-2012-04-26-at-4.20.19-PM-300x118.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"118\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Charlie Todd\'s Causing a Scene at Über Content.','','publish','open','open','','charlie-todds-causing-a-scene-at-uber-content','','','2012-04-26 20:34:02','2012-04-26 20:34:02','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=333',152,'post','',0),
	(334,2,'2012-05-01 19:02:10','2012-05-01 19:02:10','Congrats to <a href=\"www.believemedia.com\" target=\"_blank\">Believe Media</a> director <a href=\"http://www.mdbernard.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Bernard</a> for his short film, <a href=\"http://www.henryfilm.com/\" target=\"_blank\">\"Henry\" </a>and official selection and winner of the audience award at <a href=\"http://www.beverlyhillsfilmfestival.com/index.php\">The Beverly Hills Film Festival</a>.  If you have not had a chance to see this film, try to. It\'s worth the effort.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1340\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1340\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1340\" title=\"Henrysohoabb\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Henrysohoabb-300x214.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" /></a>','People love \"Henry\"','','publish','open','open','','people-love-henry','','','2012-05-01 19:02:10','2012-05-01 19:02:10','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=334',151,'post','',0),
	(335,2,'2012-09-11 22:32:27','2012-09-11 22:32:27','The Facts of Life are that Brothers and Sisters grow up and leave home, creating new families of their own.  They go from being Bosom Buddies and Partners in Crime to creating separate Brand New Lives.  But no matter what happens, Family Ties will always bind them, and siblings will always share a special love, no matter where life takes them. Sure Denise, the oldest sister on the “The Cosby Show” left home for college and starred in a series called “A Different World”… does that mean that she wasn’t still welcome in the Huxtible household?... of course not! No matter where you go or what you do, you are always family. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIt\'s with this in mind that we’d like to make an exciting announcement.  Hold on to your seats because this may come as a surprise: Diane has taken over The Family, and Chris has become a Partner at Backyard Productions!  We are thrilled for each other.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are also both excited to tell you that we will still be working together as The Family and Backyard will be continuing their successful collaboration as Family Members. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe joined forces to start The Family eight years ago.  Back then we had no idea how much fun we\'d have, and also no idea we\'d grow to love and appreciate each other as much as we do.  Because of what we have learned from each other and what we\'ve accomplished together, we are both taking on these new roles with complete confidence. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen Chris asked Diane to partner with him all those years ago (back when we were kids) it was because of her strong passion for branding, marketing, and relationship building.  She was the driving force in turning The Family from a traditional independent repping company into a unique creative service provider; helping our clients reach new heights.  She has always found her greatest joy in targeted sales, brand building and creative problem-solving, and was instrumental in pushing The Family’s offering in this direction.  Over the years, her taste level, intelligence and passion resulted in the exponential growth of all of the clients on The Family’s roster.  Diane is excited to be the sole owner and head of The Family, and will continue to help create strong lasting relationships for her Family members Backyard, Believe Media, Black Iris Music, and Imaginary Forces.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nChris’s relationship with Backyard goes back farther than he likes to admit (despite his Doogie Howser appearance, he\'s been in this business for over 20 years.)  He started repping Backyard in their earliest days, when the company was based in Chicago and had a few regional directors who were just starting their careers. Two decades later in his new role, Chris will be focusing all of his attention on energizing the Backyard brand, managing the existing directors, recruiting new talent, overseeing sales and marketing, and strengthening the company’s relationships with agencies and clients. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAnna Rotholz, The Family’s other sister, will continue in her role as kick ass rep, and is excited to grow with The Family for years to come. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWe’d both like to say that the past eight years have been the most rewarding of our careers.  We’ve both grown personally and professionally.  This is an exciting next chapter in our familial yarn, and our friendship will continue well into our golden years.  We will be announcing a little Family party to celebrate the news in the next week or two.  Points for wearing vintage Family swag!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1354\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1354\"><img src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/743377922_ukKmi-M-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"743377922_ukKmi-M\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1354\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1355\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1355\"><img src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/Image-D69F3E7.jpg-thumb_140_105.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"Image-D69F3E7.jpg-thumb_140_105\" width=\"140\" height=\"105\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1355\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1359\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1359\"><img src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/36895_405767048398_2485864_n-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"36895_405767048398_2485864_n\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1359\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?attachment_id=1360\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1360\"><img src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/8054_10150769562819058_1096596385_n-300x224.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"8054_10150769562819058_1096596385_n\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1360\" /></a>','An Announcement from The Family (trust us, you want to read this)','','publish','open','open','','an-announcement-from-the-family-trust-us-you-want-to-read-this','','','2012-09-11 22:32:27','2012-09-11 22:32:27','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=335',150,'post','',0),
