	(345,8,'2012-10-15 17:57:58','2012-10-15 17:57:58','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1530\"]\r\n\r\nHere is a sneakpeak at Allen Hughes\' (Believe Media), first solo feature, <em>Broken City, </em>a highly anticipated police drama starring Russell Crowe and Mark Wahlberg.  Allen is known films such as <em>Dead Presidents</em>, <em>Menace II Society, </em>and <em>Book of Eli</em>,<em> </em>which he directed with his brother under the Hughes Brothers moniker. With his signing to Believe, Allen is intensifying his focus on commercials and branded content, building on his already stellar career in advertising. He\'s credited with iconic campaigns for Nike, Gatorade, and Reebok.  <em>Broken City </em>will be opening in theaters January 2013, get excited!\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #999999;\">For more info, check out the links below:</span>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/04/broken-city-trailer-mark-wahlberg-russell-crowe-video_n_1940447.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.huffingtonpost.com/<wbr>2012/10/04/broken-city-<wbr>trailer-mark-wahlberg-russell-<wbr>crowe-video_n_1940447.html</wbr></wbr></wbr></a></div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://insidemovies.ew.com/2012/10/04/broken-city-trailer/\" target=\"_blank\">http://insidemovies.ew.com/<wbr>2012/10/04/broken-city-<wbr>trailer/</wbr></wbr></a></div>\r\n<span style=\"color: #1a1a1a;\">\r\n</span>','Believe Media\'s Allen Hughes returns to features with star studded film, \"Broken City.\"','','publish','open','open','','believe-medias-allen-hughes-returns-to-features-with-star-studded-film-broken-city','','','2012-10-15 17:57:58','2012-10-15 17:57:58','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=345',143,'post','',0),
	(346,8,'2012-10-24 16:57:01','2012-10-24 16:57:01','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1547\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith a new season, Imaginary Forces brings us a new reel. This latest montage highlights the company’s wide array of disciplines. From Sci-fi to MTV, life-like animation to commercial spots, the talent at Imaginary Forces can tackle any project, and tackle it well. Take a look for yourself and see they really are a force of the imagination.\r\n\r\n','A Fresh Look at Imaginary Forces!','','publish','open','open','','a-fresh-look-at-imaginary-forces','','','2012-10-24 16:57:01','2012-10-24 16:57:01','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=346',142,'post','',0),
	(347,8,'2012-10-24 17:00:21','2012-10-24 17:00:21','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1552\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEver wonder where sim cards are born? Well, with a little imagination, you just might learn from IF director, Ronnie Koff’s O2 spot. To promote the UK’s lead wireless provider, Koff created a magical factory where sim cards are made. Viewers journey through a glass machine, watching as sim cards are carried by bubble claws and sent down transparent conveyor belts. It’s like entering a new world. For 30 seconds.','Get Inside the 02 Factory!','','publish','open','open','','get-inside-the-02-factory','','','2012-10-24 17:00:21','2012-10-24 17:00:21','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=347',141,'post','',0),
	(348,8,'2012-10-26 18:18:23','2012-10-26 18:18:23','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1565\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSome books you read. Others books, you win. Check out Backyard director, Kevin Smith’s clever spot for Maryland Lottery’s new game book. Note: this kind of fun may be too much for your average bookseller and will probably require some explanation.','The Best Book Around!','','publish','open','open','','the-best-book-around','','','2012-10-26 18:18:23','2012-10-26 18:18:23','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=348',140,'post','',0),
	(349,8,'2012-10-26 21:39:24','2012-10-26 21:39:24','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1574\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe know. The Olympics were in August. And although all the medals have been won (mainly by Gabby Douglas), some spots are beautiful enough to transcend the record breaking season. Take a look at Backyard director, Alexander Paul’s, visually stunning Acer ad, “The Olympian.” Paul’s focused imagery captures the grace of champion swimmers, giving viewers a close look at the athletes’ movements. And by close look, we don’t mean slow-motion instant replay.','Re-Visit the Olympic Spirit!','','publish','open','open','','re-visit-the-olympic-spirit','','','2012-10-26 21:39:24','2012-10-26 21:39:24','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=349',139,'post','',0),
	(350,8,'2012-10-29 18:58:03','2012-10-29 18:58:03','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1581\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEven on the rainiest days, Backyard director, Kim Nguyen’s Gold’s Gym spot, “Stronger With,” will inspire a get up and go mood. Kim’s notoriously fresh style pushes viewers to ditch their couches for treadmills and crunches, to stretch their limits and get charged (not in preparations for a blackout).','Get Stronger with Gold’s Gym!','','publish','open','open','','get-stronger-with-golds-gym','','','2012-10-29 18:58:03','2012-10-29 18:58:03','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=350',138,'post','',0),
	(351,8,'2012-10-30 23:13:55','2012-10-30 23:13:55','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1588\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBackyard’s, Kim Nguyen adds a hilarious spin to Sears’ same day delivery. Kim’s witty campaign shows how sometimes you just need to shop your way, whether you’re hanging from a drainpipe or stocking up on your favorite supplies.','What You Need, When You Need it at Sears!','','publish','open','open','','what-you-need-when-you-need-it-at-sears','','','2012-10-30 23:13:55','2012-10-30 23:13:55','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=351',137,'post','',0),
	(352,8,'2012-11-07 14:10:45','2012-11-07 14:10:45','Congratulations to Believe Media director Maurice Marable for making the EBONY 2012 Power 100 list! Maurice joins the ranks of celebrities such as The Roots and Barack Obama (Michelle too) as one of the nation’s most influential African Americans. From the Dave Chappelle Show to Entourage, commercials to public interest campaigns, Maurice’s wide breadth of work has earned him this much deserved honor. Check it out <a href=\"http://www.ebony.com/entertainment-culture/ebony-reveals-its-2012-power-100-list-100\">here</a>!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Maurice Marable in EBONY’s Top 100!','','publish','open','open','','maurice-marable-in-ebonys-top-100','','','2012-11-07 14:10:45','2012-11-07 14:10:45','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=352',136,'post','',0),
	(353,8,'2012-11-09 17:39:43','2012-11-09 17:39:43','HI Family Friends,\r\n\r\nWe hope that you are all safe and sound and recovering from the storm. Mother Nature gave us a one-two punch last week with the snow. But we\'re New Yorkers and we always prevail by banding together and helping each other.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTogether with <a href=\"http://thenowcorporation.com/\">The Now Corporation</a> and their Hunger Awareness program, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Hungrr\">hungrr</a>, The Family is hosting a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/437376956320570/\">fundraiser on MONDAY, 11/12 </a>to benefit the<a href=\"https://secure3.convio.net/fbnyc/site/Donation2?idb=1474389737&amp;df_id=2781&amp;2781.donation=form1\"> FOOD BANK of NY</a> and <a href=\"https://community.njfoodbank.org/sslpage.aspx?pid=506\">FOOD BANK of NJ</a> with focus on the areas hardest hit...Staten Island, Redhook, The Rockaways, and my beloved homeland...The Jersey Shore.  It will be a fun night of comedic short films made by some fantastic local filmmakers....we\'ve got films by Tom Schiller, Tom Scharpling, Dave Laden, Jeff Feuerzeig, Lena Beug, Geremy Jasper, John Roberts, Clay Weiner, Zach Braff, Matt Lenski, and Woody Allen!\r\n\r\nIn addition, there will be some awesome treats given out for sizeable donations.  We promise you, it will be a worthwhile and super fun night.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPlease come and make a donation and enjoy some laughs. We could use them.\r\n\r\nSandy Films Night\r\n\r\n@ The Now Corporation\r\n\r\n7 West 22nd St, 6th Flr\r\n\r\nMonday, Nov 12, 7pm\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you cannot attend you can donate online by clicking the links above.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you are looking for more ways to help, former <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hollyjanebutler?fref=ts\">Family Sister Holly Butler</a> has started an amazing non profit to benefit The Rockaways, called THE ROCKAWAY RENEGADES. She has drop off locations for supplies and an in demand supply list. She also has an <a href=\"http://www.gofundme.com/rockawayrenegades\">online donation center</a>. She\'s doing great work! Way to go Sister!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Come out and Support Hurricane Sandy!','','publish','open','open','','come-out-and-support-hurricane-sandy','','','2012-11-09 17:39:43','2012-11-09 17:39:43','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=353',135,'post','',0),
	(354,8,'2012-11-23 18:35:36','2012-11-23 18:35:36','[wiredrive hidethumbs=\"off\" disablethumbs=\"on\" theme=\"inline-player\"]http://www.wdcdn.net/rss/presentation/library/client/believe/id/d5023710c1e824e9873c559d05092c66[/wiredrive]\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.believemedia.com/director.php?director_id=88\">Believe</a> (and The Family) are thrilled to welcome multitalented, multifaceted, multitasking director and photographer Anthony Mandler to the roster. With a star-studded repertoire of music videos (think Rihanna, Muse, Jay- Z, and Lana Del Rey) Anthony’s distinct style has established him as a celebrity pick for both commercial, print, and film projects.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHis work is marked by stunning visuals that, when combined with music, not only showcase products and artists but also tell a story. Full of vibrant energy, Anthony guides projects from beginning to end, from concepting and creative directing, through the end of the shoot. As a commercial director, Anthony is responsible for the P-Diddy Ciroc campaign, the latest Duracell spots, The Nike “Beautiful Monster” ads, amongst others. Believe Media is beyond excited to help Anthony build his already flourishing advertising career.','Believe Scores Anthony Mandler!','','publish','open','open','','believe-scores-anthony-mandler','','','2012-11-23 18:35:36','2012-11-23 18:35:36','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=354',134,'post','',0),
	(355,8,'2012-12-04 21:33:15','2012-12-04 21:33:15','[wiredrive hidethumbs=\"on\" disablethumbs=\"off\" theme=\"inline-player\"]http://www.wdcdn.net/rss/presentation/library/client/boxerfilms/id/d3a3004b919790d9797a900cda9d30fe[/wiredrive]\r\n\r\nBecause The Family has a Boxer—Boxer Films that is. One of the most unique, inspiring, and interesting production companies out there, we are so excited to spread the word about Boxer.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHome to a thriving commercial division, Boxer’s rolodex includes Cannes Lion wining directors. They also boast a high budget film division with several features films in pre-production (not to mention a Coup de Coeur award from The 64th Annual Cannes International Film Festival). Boxer’s thriving entertainment branch is lead by an Emmy winning producer and show runner. Plus they have a digital/interactive arm developing a never seen before tablet application. As Boxer fights their way to the top of our industry, The Family is proud to be in their corner!  <a href=\"http://www.boxerfilms.net/\">www.boxerfilms.net</a>','Put Up Your Dukes!','','publish','open','open','','put-up-your-dukes','','','2012-12-04 21:33:15','2012-12-04 21:33:15','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=355',133,'post','',0),
	(356,8,'2012-12-06 01:39:50','2012-12-06 01:39:50','We’re growing! And we’re so proud to welcome digital studio <a href=\"http://punkle.tv/\">Punkle.tv</a> in to The Family. We have partnered with Punkle\'s owner and creative force, Matt Long to develop and launch this exciting company. Matt may just be the only former chef and organic farmer to successfully cross over into web, interactive design and innovation industry...and definitely the first one to be at the helm of a digital design and production studio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMatt\'s creativity, ingenuity, sheer brain-power, and access to unique resources and talent make Punkle a distinct company in the interactive field. Stay tuned for some fun from Punkle. Fun that begins with their inaugural R&amp;D piece, launching just before Christmas.','The Family gets Punk\'d...in a good way.','','publish','open','open','','the-family-gets-punkd-in-a-good-way','','','2012-12-06 01:39:50','2012-12-06 01:39:50','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=356',132,'post','',0),
	(357,8,'2012-12-10 18:57:23','2012-12-10 18:57:23','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1641\"]\r\n\r\nKeep an eye out for IF director Miguel Lee’s new opening sequence for the CBS hit show, <em>Person of Interest</em>. Through sound effects and elaborate graphical tool kits, Miguel perfectly captures the web of surveillance that lies at the center of this show. Not to mention the just plain creepy idea that Michael Emerson (Ben from Lost) and his team of “Big Brothers” are watching us. Always.','They’re Watching….','','publish','open','open','','theyre-watching','','','2012-12-10 18:57:23','2012-12-10 18:57:23','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=357',131,'post','',0),
