	(361,8,'2012-12-12 19:40:45','2012-12-12 19:40:45','[jwplayer mediaid=\"1668\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOr at least it makes you sweat. And unless your one of those blessed creatures whose sweat smells like flowers, you’ll appreciate Backyard director Kevin Smith’s latest Secret spot. With a candid and just plain loveable narrator, this commercial puts a humorous spin on those moments that make us all sweat a little a more.','Stress Stinks!','','publish','open','open','','stress-stinks','','','2012-12-12 19:40:45','2012-12-12 19:40:45','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=361',129,'post','',0),
	(362,8,'2013-01-15 19:55:47','2013-01-15 19:55:47','Who needs a co-director brother when you have a surrogate family right here!  Allen Hughes of Believe Media is striking out on his own, directing his first solo feature film, \"Broken City.\"  The movie and Hughes himself are getting tons of buzz and we couldn\'t be more excited and giddy over its release.  Check out these two pieces about him at <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2013/01/13/movies/broken-city-is-directed-solo-by-allen-hughes.html?pagewanted=all\">The New York Times</a> and <a href=\"http://www.deadline.com/2012/11/mike-fleming-interviews-broken-city-helmer-allen-hughes-on-his-first-solo-film/#utm_source=sailthru&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=breakingnewsalert\">Deadline.com</a>.\r\n\r\nThen enjoy the trailer below to get a glimpse of Mark Wahlberg, Russell Crowe and Catherine Zeta-Jones in this gritty crime thriller.  And don\'t forget check it out in theaters January 18th.\r\n\r\n[youtube KaD6Ve4FDLA nolink]','Allen Hughes\' Real Family','','publish','open','open','','allen-hughes-real-family','','','2013-01-15 19:55:47','2013-01-15 19:55:47','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=362',128,'post','',0),
	(363,8,'2013-01-25 17:25:26','2013-01-25 17:25:26','Is kissing losing its appeal thanks to the increasing trend in men\'s facial hair?  Backyard\'s Xander ponders this conundrum with his quirky documentary below.  Featuring a charming host with priceless reaction takes, we learn new terms like \"burn beard\" (the redness women suffer from kissing a man with too much stubble), and man\'s failed attempt at peacocking by growing outlandish mustaches like the \"walrus.\"  Whether facial hair and desirability are linked we may never know, but this delightful doc surely makes you wonder.\r\n\r\n[youtube dtTZURt4Hkc nolink]','Pucker Up!','','publish','open','open','','pucker-up','','','2013-01-25 17:25:26','2013-01-25 17:25:26','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=363',127,'post','',0),
	(364,8,'2013-01-25 17:26:03','2013-01-25 17:26:03','Before you start thinking there\'s some kinkiness going on here at The Family... check out Backyard Director Jesper Ericstam\'s latest for Ikea. With his special brand of subtle,warm humor and beautiful film, Jespers puts a twist on the all too familiar idea of a kid running into a parents\' room to sleep, ousting one said parent.  Jesper lets us know that no matter where (or with whom) you find yourself sleeping/tossing/turning/cuddling, you can sleep tight while resting your head on an Ikea pillow, or wrapped in an Ikea blanket, or fast asleep on an Ikea bed.\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"1740\"]\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Family that sleeps together...','','publish','open','open','','family-that-sleeps-together','','','2013-01-25 17:26:03','2013-01-25 17:26:03','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=364',126,'post','',0),
	(365,8,'2013-01-25 17:26:25','2013-01-25 17:26:25','<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">Paging Dr. CB2!  The design house chain took a note from our familial pages and designed a line specifically with us in mind.  Thanks to our new Family rug, our office is shining like Janice Dickenson after her latest chemical peel.  Shout out to assistant extraordinaire, Rachel, for hanging the 65lb beast with only one incidence of hammering her thumb.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1727\" title=\"1\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"621\" height=\"466\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">Equally fun is our new art collection, an eclectic menagerie featuring one super studly Family member.  Can you find Waldo?</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1732\" title=\"2\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/21.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"613\" height=\"460\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">Stop by to check out our new upgrades!</p>','Family Face Lift','','publish','open','open','','family-face-lift-2','','','2013-01-25 17:26:25','2013-01-25 17:26:25','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=365',125,'post','',0),
	(366,8,'2013-01-25 17:26:46','2013-01-25 17:26:46','<img class=\" wp-image-1749 alignleft\" title=\"kiefdavidson\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/kiefdavidson.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"139\" height=\"209\" />\r\n\r\nKief Davidson\'s documentary short film, \"Open Heart,\" has been nominated for an Academy Award!  An Oscar, the golden statue, the big cheese.  That\'s right, Believe\'s very own Kief Davidson is an Academy Award nominated director.  We are so proud of his accomplishments and wish him the very best on his big night.  Be sure to tune in to the awards ceremony on Sunday, February 24 when we\'ll have all our finger and toes crossed for Kief\'s triumph.\r\n\r\nClick <a href=\"http://openheartfilm.com\">here</a> to learn more about the film and its esteemed director.','Just call him Gold, Mr. Gold','','publish','open','open','','just-call-him-gold-mr-gold','','','2013-01-25 17:26:46','2013-01-25 17:26:46','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=366',124,'post','',0),
