	(376,8,'2013-02-27 22:34:31','2013-02-27 22:34:31','Floria Sigismondi from Believe Media is raking in the press for her latest collaboration with the coolest musician on the planet.  The \"video\" is really more like a short film set to music, featuring the the man himself, his doppleganger, Tilda Swinton, and a couple of Bowie-esque models.  The story is like a \"Stepford Wives\" meets \"Being John Malkovich\" and Sigismondi expertly captures our eerie obsession with celebrity.\r\n\r\nAnd check out the links below for a taste of all the recognition:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://entertainment.time.com/2013/02/26/david-bowie-and-tilda-swinton-make-sweet-music-video-together/\">Time</a>     <a href=\"http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2013/02/david-bowie-new-music-a-decade-later/\">ABC News</a>     <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/blogs/allsongs/2013/02/25/172904974/david-bowies-new-song-is\">NPR</a>      <a href=\"http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2013/02/26/david-bowie-the-stars-video/1947859/\">USA Today</a>    <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/musicblog/2013/feb/26/david-bowie-stars-out-tonight-video\">The Guardian</a>     <a href=\"http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1549902/david-bowie-drops-new-song-video-for-the-stars-are-out-tonight\">Billboard</a>      <a href=\"http://www.vulture.com/2013/02/the-stars-are-out-tonight-video-david-bowie-tilda-swinton.html\">Vulture</a>\r\n\r\n[youtube gH7dMBcg-gE nolink]','Being David Bowie','','publish','open','open','','being-david-bowie-2','','','2013-02-27 22:34:31','2013-02-27 22:34:31','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=376',116,'post','',0),
