	(378,8,'2013-04-02 16:22:43','2013-04-02 16:22:43','Boxer Films has a new development arm and they\'re making a big splash with the launch.  The new division, dubbed <a href=\"http://boxerfilms.net/digital/\">Random Content</a>, has just released the iBook for the legendary Carl Reiner\'s memoir, <em>Carl Reiner: I Remember Me</em>.  The iBook combines text with an assortment of streaming and image materials including film clips, pictures and motion picture excerpts.  The features also include touch and slide timeline navigation, embedded video content, photo scrapbook with touch zoom, optional narration by Reiner himself, and changeable photo wallpaper backgrounds.  Cool, right?  And if that wasn\'t enough, Random Content plans to announce more such projects in the future.  Read more about the new venture <a href=\"http://www.shootonline.com/go/index.php?name=Release&amp;op=view&amp;id=rs-web3-1235277-1363994807-2\">here</a>.','Boxer Grows a New Arm','','publish','open','open','','boxer-grows-a-new-arm','','','2013-04-02 16:22:43','2013-04-02 16:22:43','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=378',114,'post','',0),
	(379,8,'2013-04-02 16:23:07','2013-04-02 16:23:07','Remember <em>Food, Inc</em>?  The compelling, gut-wrenching and award winning documentary that turned you into a vegetarian (at least for a week)?  Well, that unforgettable film, among many other great works, was directed by one Robert Kenner and Boxer Films has got him!  The director just joined the roster at the ever versatile production house and we\'re sure to see even more special work from the team.  Welcome to the Family, Robert!  Read more about Robert\'s accomplishments <a href=\"http://www.shots.net/news/people-moves/80921/robert-kenner-joins-boxer.html\">here</a>.','New Family Member Alert!','','publish','open','open','','new-family-member-alert','','','2013-04-02 16:23:07','2013-04-02 16:23:07','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=379',113,'post','',0),
