	(390,8,'2013-06-03 17:50:03','2013-06-03 17:50:03','Xander makes us all feel out of shape with his latest spot for ASICS called \"What\'s Next.\"  The <a href=\"http://backyard.com/directors/xander\">Backyard</a> director features Olympic athletes including Lolo Jones, Bryan Clay, and April Steiner Bennett training as hard as they can and awing us in the process.  Xander\'s goal with the spot was to \"capture raw athleticism in the most authentic way possible, matching the energy they feel in training. That meant keeping our energy up and urging them to train as they do for competition.  The locations we found also helped put them in that state of mind.\"  The hard work has paid off and the spot is garnering tons of buzz including recognition on <a href=\"http://screenmag.com/story/2013/may/13/10184/\">screenmag.com</a>, <a href=\"http://www.bestadsontv.com/ad/53397/ASICS-Whats-Next\">bestadsontv.com</a>, <a href=\"http://www.campaignbrief.us/2013/05/asics-launches-whats-next-tv-c.html\">campaignbrief.us</a>, and <a href=\"http://lbbonline.com/news/asics-inspire-athletes-to-chase-whats-next/\">lbbonline.com</a>.  Check out the spot and just try not to feel bad about sitting on the couch and eating the crumbs at the bottom of the potato chip bag!\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2059\"]','And you thought your workout was hard','','publish','open','open','','and-you-thought-your-workout-was-hard','','','2013-06-03 17:50:03','2013-06-03 17:50:03','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=390',103,'post','',0),
