	(396,2,'2013-06-14 20:27:13','2013-06-14 20:27:13','<div>We love it when we come across a talent that is so vast we have to create two different reels to convey its greatness. This could not be more evidenced this week as the two sides of Boxer\'s director <a href=\"http://boxerfilms.net/commercials/director/rodrigo-garcia-saiz/\">Rodrigo Garcia Saiz</a> are on display in the trades with the debut of two vastly different spots. In the gripping and hilarious misdirect “Boxer,” Saiz chronicles the struggles, triumphs, and ultimate failure of a fighter’s training, all culminating to one pivotal moment: the victorious consumption of a Sadia Hot Pocket. A darker piece, the anticipatory “Playground” has us reeling in suspense for a young boy desperately attempting to escape a mysterious gunman. A PSA announcement for Mexican organization Todo Dias Es El Dia (Everyday is the Day to Not Discriminate), Saiz’s touching portrayal helps to raise awareness of bullying with its strongly executed message. Simply put: we can’t wait to see what this family member does next. Check out the spots (and some rave reviews) below.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: arial,verdana,helvetica,sans-serif;\">\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-family: arial,verdana,helvetica,sans-serif;\">\"Boxer\" </span></div>\r\n<a href=\"http://screenmag.com/story/2013/jun/05/10222/\" target=\"_blank\">http://screenmag.com/story/2013/jun/05/10222/</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"color: #1155cc; font-family: verdana;\">\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div>“Playground”</div>\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.shootonline.com/go/news-view.rs-web3-3765901-1369958298-2.The-Best-Work-You-May-Never-See--Todos-Los-Dias-Es-El-Dia-s--Playground-.html\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.shootonline.com/go/news-view.rs-web3-3765901-1369958298-2.The-Best-Work-You-May-Never-See--Todos-Los-Dias-Es-El-Dia-s--Playground-.html</a></div>','The Two Faces of the Three Named Man','','publish','open','open','','the-two-faces-of-the-three-named-man','','','2013-06-14 20:27:13','2013-06-14 20:27:13','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=396',97,'post','',0),
	(397,8,'2013-07-02 20:11:18','2013-07-02 20:11:18','Another successful year in Cannes topped off with a momentous birthday for our top sister, Diane!  Cannes was a lot of work, a lot of fun, and a lot of Lions (woohoo!).\r\n\r\nTo start, there was favorite family member Chris Zander guest contributing for Agency Spy.  In his posts he muses about why it\'s still worth going back to Cannes year after year, dancing, and South Africa.  You can learn more about the Backyarder <a href=\"http://www.mediabistro.com/agencyspy/our-cannes-contributor-chimes-in-pre-flight_b49704\">here</a>, <a href=\"http://www.mediabistro.com/agencyspy/and-now-a-quick-cannes-report_b49806\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://www.mediabistro.com/agencyspy/and-now-a-quick-cannes-report-wednesday-recap-edition-with-dj_b49890#more-49890\">here</a>.\r\n\r\nAnd now back to those Lions...our family members surely did represent!  Beloved <em>Boxer</em> <em>Films</em> director Rodrigo Garcia Saiz took home three, yes <strong>three</strong>, of the coveted prizes.  Winning <strong>Silver</strong> for AMIS \"Discussion,\"\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2082\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Bronze</strong> for Anti Discrimination \"Playground,\"\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2088\"]\r\n\r\nand <strong>Bronze</strong> for Parental Control Board \"Pool,\"  cut by Family Member <em>Union Editorial</em> (Jay Friedkin) which makes it a double Bronze, two headed Lion win.\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2085\"]\r\n\r\nOverall, it was a very memorable trip and we can\'t wait until next year.  Au revoir!','Cannes Do!','','publish','open','open','','cannes-do','','','2013-07-02 20:11:18','2013-07-02 20:11:18','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=397',96,'post','',0),
	(398,8,'2013-07-18 20:14:05','2013-07-18 20:14:05','Rodrigo Garcia Saiz is getting the recognition he deserves for his stellar outing at Cannes this year.  After bringing home another 3 lions in 2013, Shoot Online is giving the Boxer Films director his due.  Read the article <a href=\"http://www.shootonline.com/go/index.php?name=Release&amp;op=view&amp;id=rs-web3-1265388-1372807511-2\">here</a> and watch all his winners together <a href=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/?p=2079\">here</a>.  Plus he\'s a cutie so enjoy his picture below!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2099\" title=\"Rodrigo\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Rodrigo-300x270.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"270\" />','Dios Mio!','','publish','open','open','','dios-mio','','','2013-07-18 20:14:05','2013-07-18 20:14:05','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=398',95,'post','',0),
	(399,8,'2013-07-18 20:14:52','2013-07-18 20:14:52','Now THIS is what a car commercial should be!  Let the car do the talking and let Michelle Dougherty and Karin Fong from Imaginary Forces do the directing.  This dynamic duo have created a truly memorable spot for Lexus with their latest work titled \"Intensity.\" The spot starts off with a question: What if we could engineer a feeling?  That\'s exactly what they do using stunning visual imagery laced with pulsating music and sound.  It\'s an adrenaline rush for the eyes and you may just want to crawl through your screen and into the driver\'s seat.\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2103\"]','Imagine: Intensity','','publish','open','open','','imagine-intensity','','','2013-07-18 20:14:52','2013-07-18 20:14:52','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=399',94,'post','',0),
	(400,8,'2013-07-18 20:15:51','2013-07-18 20:15:51','When dealing with an epic battle of man versus machine, there\'s no better powerhouse than Imaginary Forces to create the opening title sequence for Guillermo del Toro\'s much anticipated new movie<em>, </em>\"Pacific Rim.\"  But what\'s more is that IF also created the much talked about ending title sequence.  In an effort to keep viewers in their seats to catch a secret added scene after the credits (sequel, anyone?), IF does such a masterful job that they could be at the forefront of a new movie trend.  The visuals are so stunning and the animation so real, it\'s not enough for a movie to just end...dazzle \'em til the lights come up!  Check out the praise IF is receiving for their latest endeavor <a href=\"http://www.ventilate.ca/2013/07/16/imaginary-forces-pacific-rim-titles/#more-13614\">here</a>, <a href=\"http://www.awn.com/news/business/imaginary-forces-completes-pacific-rim-title-sequences\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://www.giantfreakinrobot.com/scifi/watch-pacific-rims-stunning-opening-closing-credits.html\">here</a>, and check out both videos below to see for yourself.\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2108\"]\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2110\"]','Guillermo del Toro + Imaginary Forces = Crazy Awesomeness','','publish','open','open','','guillermo-del-toro-imaginary-forces-crazy-awesomeness','','','2013-07-18 20:15:51','2013-07-18 20:15:51','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=400',93,'post','',0),
	(401,8,'2013-07-29 19:08:07','2013-07-29 19:08:07','Day in and day out we slave away and do the hard work simply because we love it.  But there\'s no greater day when you finally get recognition for every drop of blood, sweat or tear.  And today is just one of those days for Union Editorial\'s Sloane Klevin.  The masterful editor has just been nominated for an EMMY!  That\'s right, TV\'s top honor, the creme de la creme.  On the heels of Union\'s Lion win in Cannes, Klevin is keeping the good news coming with her nomination for Outstanding Picture Editing for Nonfiction Programming for HBO\'s \"Mea Maxima Culpa: Silence In The House Of God.\"  Well done Sloane, we\'re rootin for ya!!!\r\n\r\n[youtube OSstCtWl54w nolink]','Union Editorial\'s Sloane Klevin Gets an Emmy Nod!','','publish','open','open','','union-editorials-sloane-klevin-gets-an-emmy-nod','','','2013-07-29 19:08:07','2013-07-29 19:08:07','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=401',92,'post','',0),
	(402,8,'2013-07-29 19:10:27','2013-07-29 19:10:27','Congratulations to Believe directors <a href=\"http://www.believemedia.com/floria-sigismondi/\">Floria Sigismondi</a> and <a href=\"http://www.believemedia.com/anthony-mandler/\">Anthony Mandler</a> on their 2013 MTV VMA nominations sweep.  The pair were honored with a total of <em><strong>9 noms</strong></em> between them <strong>(even sharing the coveted Video of the Year category)</strong> for the memorable visuals they have crafted for some of the biggest names in music today.  The MTV Music Video Awards air live on August 25.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2129\" title=\"floria\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/floria.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"516\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2130\" title=\"mandler\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/mandler.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"498\" height=\"859\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Believe Media Rules the VMAs','','publish','open','open','','believe-media-rules-the-vmas','','','2013-07-29 19:10:27','2013-07-29 19:10:27','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=402',91,'post','',0),
	(403,8,'2013-07-29 19:15:27','2013-07-29 19:15:27','We all have that special t-shirt we can\'t ever part with.  Without sounding the \"hoarder\" alarm, we\'ve worn the heck out of said t-shirt and Downy\'s new ad supports our need to hold on.  Edited by <a href=\"unioneditorial.com\">Union Editorial</a>\'s Laura Milstein, this memorable spot features one such t-shirt loving example even passing down through the generations.  It\'s so cute, <a href=\"http://www.mediabistro.com/agencyspy/grey-worldwide-new-york-downy-tell-a-t-shirt-love-story_b51190\">Agency Spy</a> wrote a little piece on it.  Check it out and enjoy the spot below!\r\n\r\n[youtube fL9Tfu8Vpqg nolink]','A Downy Love Story','','publish','open','open','','a-downy-love-story','','','2013-07-29 19:15:27','2013-07-29 19:15:27','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=403',90,'post','',0),
	(404,8,'2013-08-05 20:56:50','2013-08-05 20:56:50','<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.believemedia.com/antony-hoffman/\">Antony Hoffman</a> is known worldwide as an acclaimed director, and China is taking notice.  He\'s been working there so much that he\'s even taken up residence and making a giant mark on the growing advertising industry there.  So much so that <em><strong>Shots</strong></em> took notice and interviewed him on the emerging empire. Read the great write up on his experiences directing in China below.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-2163\" title=\"shots profile\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/shots-profile-746x1024.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"746\" height=\"1024\" /></p>','Year of the Snake? More like the year of the Hoffman!','','publish','open','open','','antony-hoffman-is-the-man','','','2013-08-05 20:56:50','2013-08-05 20:56:50','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=404',89,'post','',0),
	(405,8,'2013-08-05 21:01:31','2013-08-05 21:01:31','<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2170\" title=\"Photo by Brandon Joseph Baker\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/SloaneKlevin_MG_672851f68803ad260.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"242\" height=\"305\" />Sloane Klevin may already be an Emmy award winner but she\'s over the moon to be nominated<em> again</em>.  Shoot online did a great interview with <a href=\"http://www.unioneditorial.com/\">Union Editorial\'s</a> Emmy nominee about the joy of working on documentary films, the challenge of cutting together deaf subjects, and the creative freedom of working with someone like director Alex Gibney.  Enjoy the full story <a href=\"http://www.shootonline.com/go/news-view.rs-web3-2524281-1375110275-2.The-Road-To-Emmy--Part-4--A-Look-At-The-Long-And-Short-of-Editing.html\">here</a>.','More accolades for editor Sloane Klevin','','publish','open','open','','more-accolades-for-editor-sloane-klevin','','','2013-08-05 21:01:31','2013-08-05 21:01:31','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=405',88,'post','',0);
