	(406,8,'2013-08-22 19:30:02','2013-08-22 19:30:02','The incredibly talented folks over at <a href=\"http://barkingowlsound.com/\">Barking Owl</a> have put their blood, sweat and tears into the latest Nike spot, and it was worth every drop.  They spent two weeks slaving over a spot that came to them with no production sound at all.  That means that literally everything you hear, they created!  So it comes as no surprise that people are taking notice.  <a href=\"http://www.adweek.com/news/advertising-branding/ad-day-nike-tests-your-limits-it-redefines-just-do-it-25-151974\">Ad Week</a> wrote a glowing review and named it Ad of the Day.  Just take a look (and listen) for yourselves!\r\n\r\n[youtube aPkyPdubqDs nolink]','Barking Owl Just Did It','','publish','open','open','','barking-owl-just-did-it','','','2013-08-22 19:30:02','2013-08-22 19:30:02','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=406',87,'post','',0),
	(407,8,'2013-09-09 20:24:42','2013-09-09 20:24:42','Have you noticed how catchy the song in the new <a href=\"http://adsoftheworld.com/media/tv/nissan_versa_door_trip\">Nissan Versa</a> commercial is?  Well you\'re not alone.  <a href=\"http://barkingowlsound.com/\">Barking Owl</a> has another hit on their hands!  They have been garnering so much praise for their latest effort that the song is being turned into a full length track.  If the inspiration for this ad was \"You\'re happiest doing what you love,\" then it\'s plain to see that the folks over at Barking Owl LOVE making music!!\r\n\r\n[youtube uBSWHk4Oezo nolink]','Clap Your Hands','','publish','open','open','','clap-your-hands','','','2013-09-09 20:24:42','2013-09-09 20:24:42','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=407',86,'post','',0),
	(408,8,'2013-10-01 14:53:31','2013-10-01 14:53:31','There\'s little to laugh at when disaster strikes but even in the worst of times you can\'t lose your sense of humor.  <a href=\"http://backyard.com/directors/rob-pritts\">Rob Pritts</a> from <a href=\"http://backyard.com/\">Backyard Productions</a> keeps this in mind for his comedic but informative PSA for the Red Cross.  He takes the angle of what <em>not</em> to pack in an emergency kit, keeping the tone light hearted...because who doesn\'t think to pack a game of Operation as a first aid kit?!  <a href=\"http://web11.shootonline.com/go/index.php?name=Articles&amp;op=view&amp;id=rs-web3-4499950-1378480493-2\">Shoot Online</a> named it \"The Best Work You May Never See,\" and <a href=\"http://screenmag.com/story/2013/sep/13/10392/\">Screen Mag</a>, <a href=\"http://www.adforum.com/creative-work/ad/player/34489793\">Ad Forum</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.campaignbrief.us/2013/09/backyards-rob-pritts-shoots-ne.html\">Campaign Brief</a> all wrote it up too.  Check it out!\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2205\"]','Water, Flashlight and Nun Chucks?','','publish','open','open','','water-flashlight-and-nun-chucks','','','2013-10-01 14:53:31','2013-10-01 14:53:31','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=408',85,'post','',0),
	(409,8,'2013-10-01 14:53:51','2013-10-01 14:53:51','Oh hello there Sloane Klevin, is that an Emmy in your hand or are you just happy to see us?  Must be both cause that IS an Emmy in your hand and you look damn happy about it!  As you should be!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur deepest congratulations to Union Editorial\'s Sloane Klevin and her well deserved win for Outstanding Picture Editing for Nonfiction Programming for HBO’s “Mea Maxima Culpa: Silence In The House Of God.”  Well done, we\'re so proud of you!!!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2214\" title=\"IMG_7268\" src=\"http://www.thefamilynyc.com/previous_site_2/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/IMG_7268.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" />','Congrats Sloane!','','publish','open','open','','congrats-sloane','','','2013-10-01 14:53:51','2013-10-01 14:53:51','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=409',84,'post','',0),
	(410,8,'2013-10-01 14:54:07','2013-10-01 14:54:07','<a href=\"http://backyard.com/directors/kim--nguyen\">Kim Nguyen</a> has her uber talented finger on the pulse of the millennial generation and it shows in her work. In her latest spot for \'47 Brand, the <a href=\"http://backyard.com/\">Backyard</a> director says she \"wanted to capture an authentic pocket of youth culture in anywhere USA\" and boy did she.  For something as simple as a baseball cap, Nguyen wove a story full of teenage angst and insecurity into one 30 second spot.  Read about her work with the Fantastical <a href=\"http://www.campaignbrief.us/2013/09/backyards-nguyen-gets-guy-out.html?utm_source=twitterfeed&amp;utm_medium=facebook\">here</a> and check out the spot below.\r\n\r\n[jwplayer mediaid=\"2267\"]','Brothers in Hats','','publish','open','open','','brothers-in-hats','','','2013-10-01 14:54:07','2013-10-01 14:54:07','',0,'http://thefamily.dev/?p=410',83,'post','',0),
